title: banana tea muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
In a mixing bowl, combine the egg, oil and bananas.
Add dry ingredients to the egg mixture, mixing only enough to dampen all the flour.
Turn into well-greased muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni 'n cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; stretch each triangle slightly.
Place 3 slices of pepperoni, slightly overlapping, on center of each triangle.
Top each with about 1 tablespoon cheese.	Roll up, starting at shortest side of triangle and rolling to opposite point.
Place rolls point side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with spaghetti sauce for dipping.
Yields 8 snacks.

title: darrell's venison stew
directions: Roll meat in flour.
Brown in shortening in a large skillet. Add water, wine, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Low heat and simmer 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cook until vegetables are done.
Add frozen vegetables and more water if needed.
When vegetables are done, serve with French bread.

title: bonnie's 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Peel and finely chop tomatoes.
Stir together with chopped chili peppers, onion, green pepper and lemon juice.
Add parsley, garlic and pepper.
Place 1 cup tomato mixture in blender or processor.
Blend until just pureed.
Also blend in tomato sauce at the same time.
Stir all ingredients together.
Chill and store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Use as dip for chips or topper for main dishes.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Combine 1/2 oleo, 1/2 cocoa, shortening and water in pan.
Bring to slow boil.
Stir in flour mixture well.
Will be stiff.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Pour in cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and chill 4 hours.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease angel cake pan or Bundt pan.
Arrange frozen rolls in bottom and layer if necessary.
Sprinkle rolls with dry pudding. Bring butter, sugar and cinnamon to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and set on countertop until morning.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on plate while still warm.

title: onion-dill dip
directions: Mix together in blender or food processor all ingredients. Process 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Store covered in the refrigerator.
Serve with raw vegetables, fat-free crackers or guiltless chips.

title: rum cake
directions: Heat 5 minutes, then cool. Add 1/2 cup dark rum and pour over cake slowly.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease 13 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts on batter and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Dump onto dish towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll while hot; unroll after cool.

title: middle age spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw cauliflower or broccoli.

title: sims fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk. Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme. Beat with mixer. Add nuts and vanilla. Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls or spread in a pan.

title: aunt dolores' orange chicken
directions: Dust chicken pieces with flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Brown chicken pieces in oil.
Saute onion in same pan.
Add orange juice concentrate, sugar, oregano, nutmeg and water into the oil.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate 1 tablespoon peel and squeeze 4 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice from lemon; set aside.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: easy cheese sauce
directions: Mix together; heat on low heat until blended and the cheese melts.
Great on vegetables.

title: aunt mary's chili
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat. Add green pepper, onion, garlic and salt. Cook a short time. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well. Cook for about 45 minutes on low heat. Serve with sour cream or shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: fettuccine with shiitake mushrooms and rosemary(great summer recipe!)
directions: In small bowl, toss mushrooms with lemon juice and set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars, salt and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir together dry ingredients in separate bowl, then slowly add to other ingredients.
Dough should hold together and stay firm.
Pinch off dough into walnut-size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Press down with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: laura's cherry brownies
directions: Stir cake mix, pie filling, almond extract and eggs together. Pour into 15 x 10-inch greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Press crescent roll dough into bottom of pie dish.
Sprinkle half of crushed Fritos onto dough.
Fry ground beef (like Sloppy Joes).
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour meat into pie dish.
Top with sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until crescent dough is golden.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and sour cream.

title: zucchini apple bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla. Beat until thick.
Stir in zucchini.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add the apples.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: lemon-pineapple cheese cake
directions: *Chill milk in freezer.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut up a fryer. Wash in clear water. Mix the flour, black pepper, red pepper and "no salt." Mix dry ingredients in brown sack with dried chicken. Shake off excess flour. Grease iron frying pan over medium heat. Add vegetable oil. Slowly brown chicken on all sides.

title: strawberry fruit spread
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add gelatin mixture, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour strawberry mixture into sterilized glass jars; cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 4 to 6 hours or until mixture is thoroughly chilled.
Store in refrigerator for up to 1 month.
Yield:
3 half pints (about 7 calories per tablespoon).

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir soda into flour.
Mix flour and buttermilk to creamed mix.
Add bananas. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Press with a fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Sift flour and salt, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in airtight container.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak strips
in butter;	remove from pan.
Brown onions, then mushrooms;
adding
more
butter
as needed.
Add soup; allow to sit over
low heat for approximately 5 minutes. Add sour cream and enough
flour to thicken gravy.
Bring to a low boil; add meat strips.
Heat and serve.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almond bark, in large mixing bowl. Melt almond bark in double boiler or microwave until creamy.
Mix all other ingredients in with almond bark.

title: chicken dijon in phyllo
directions: In a large skillet, melt half the butter over medium heat. Saute chicken just until it turns white, but not long enough to cook through.
Remove from heat.
Drain chicken and transfer to mixing bowl.
Stir in mustard and heavy cream.
Chill for a few hours.

title: bayou red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water. Pour into large heavy pan or dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Simmer 3 hr or until beans are tender. Remove ham bone, cut off meat and add to beans. Add water when necessary during cooking. Water should barely cover beans at end of cooking time. Remove 1 c beans and mash to paste. Add to beans and stir until liquid is thickened. Serve over hot white rice. 6 servings.

title: diet strawberry delight
directions: Half the angel food cake so you will have two rounds.
Put 1/2 in a big bowl.
Mix the boxes of jello with 1 cup boiling water and stir, then add strawberries and let stand until you make the pudding by the directions on the box.
Put half the jello over the first half of cake.
Put pudding on top of strawberries, then put the other half of the cake, strawberries and pudding.
Put in refrigerator to set about 1 hour or until you want to spread the carton of Cool Whip on top.
Spoon it out into dishes when serving.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat and salt and pepper.
Add to the rest of the ingredients and cook until cabbage is done.

title: shrimp-pork egg rolls
directions: In a large pot, combine cabbage, celery and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cook about 5 minutes or until tender. Drain in colander and cool.
Press vegetables against side of colander to extract liquid.
Vegetables should look dry.

title: fresh apple cake(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, eggs and oil.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: bacon cheese bake
directions: Layer cubed bread in buttered 9 x 13 pan. Cover bread with bacon. Beat eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Pour over layers. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Drizzle margarine over cheese. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook hamburger until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cheeses, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Spread 1/2 the noodles in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Moisten noodles with some of the meat sauce.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles, then meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: twinkie filling
directions: Boil until thick the flour and water; cool.
Add sugar and salt.
Using a mixer, add vanilla, margarine and Crisco.
Cream together, mixing until smooth.
Use as a filling between cake layers and fill chocolate cupcakes with it.
Really good.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or 12-cup tube pan.
Mix cake mix and Jell-O in a bowl.
Mix together eggs, water and oil.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Add the lemon juice and mix at medium speed with a mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into the prepared Bundt pan.
Place in preheated oven and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
When pick comes out clean, it's done.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then turn out on a cooling rack. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: delicious broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as per directions on box.
Saute onion and celery in butter or margarine.
In large bowl, combine strained broccoli and sauteed onion and celery.
Add soup, mushrooms and stuffing (reserve some stuffing to sprinkle on top), stir.
Put mixture into 3-quart casserole, sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serves many!

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small flowerets.
Wash and drain thoroughly.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar into a sauce. Pour over the vegetables.
Marinate overnight, turning several times to be sure it is coated.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in small amount of corn oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Stir in mixture of barbecue sauce, pineapple juice, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes.
Add pineapple and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.

title: grandmother's buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together and add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.

title: irene's sweet potatoes
directions: Mash up potatoes. Save out part of the juice until you see if you need it. Add rest of ingredients and mix well with potato masher until it resembles regular mashed potatoes. Pour into greased casserole. Add marshmallows on top, if desired. Bake at 350° until set (about 20 to 30 minutes) and marshmallows are browned.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut into small pieces and boil in salted water until done (approximately 20 to 25 minutes). Drain. Grate 3 of the hard-boiled eggs. Mix potatoes, eggs and remaining ingredients. Mix well and place in serving dish. Slice remaining egg and place on top of salad. If desired, sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: birdseed for people(yield: 10 cups)
directions: Combine cereal, peanuts, raisins and candies in airtight container.
Shake to mix.

title: whole hog "pig pickin"
directions: Heat and stir until butter melts.

title: tangy oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and spices.
Put crackers in paper sack or bowl.
Pour oil mixture over crackers.
Shake in sack or stir in bowl.

title: carrot salad
directions: Prepare a bed of lettuce.
Combine the first five ingredients and scoop onto lettuce.
Pour your favorite dressing over top. Serves two.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together and store back in cracker box or container and store in refrigerator.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, lemon juice, raspberries and pineapple (do not drain juice).
Pour half the mixture in mold.
Let set until hard.
Put layer of sour cream on top of it.
Add remaining jello mixture.
Fits large mold or 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add rice, bouillon and mushrooms and stir until heated.
Pour into casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes (until rice is tender).

title: plum nutty cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and plums.
Beat about 4 minutes or until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Bake in a greased tube pan in 325° oven for 75 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, glaze top with mixture of powdered sugar and water or milk.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken in chicken broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces; combine with celery, almonds, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Add mushrooms and water chestnuts; toss with mayonnaise and soup. Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: aubergine salad(lebanese; international; heart healthy)
directions: Grill the aubergines so that you can skin them. Mash the pulp with all the other ingredients to make a paste. Serve on lettuce leaves, garnished with olives and slices of tomato and green pepper. It can be spread on bread or eaten with a fork. You can garnish with chopped parsley and onions.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, water and gelatin together and bring to a rolling boil.
Mix whipped topping according to package directions, then add cream cheese and whip until stiff.
When gelatin mixture is partially set, fold in the whipped mixture and return to refrigerator to set for several hours.

title: festive green beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Spray a cookie sheet with cooking spray and place the diced potatoes in a single layer (try to keep the skins facing down). Roast until fork-tender and lightly brown; hard to give a time, depending on the thickness of the potatoes. You can do this in batches if necessary for space. Place cooked potatoes in a large bowl. Add in cooked eggs, sliced scallions and bacon. Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste. Add in Miracle Whip to desired consistency. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: red top salad
directions: Pour over top of lime jello and refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve 10 wafers for garnish.
Mix 1/2 c. sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Blend in 3 egg yolks and milk. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly for 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Spread small amount of custard on bottom of 1 1/2 qt. dish; cover with layer of wafers and a layer of sliced bananas.
Pour about 1/3 custard over bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make 3 layers of each, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add remaining 1/4 c. sugar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Spoon on top of custard, spreading to cover entire surface and sealing well to edges.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Cool slightly or refrigerate.
Garnish with reserved wafers.

title: southwest dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream on low until well blended.
By hand, stir in chilies, pepperoni, onion and chives.
Spoon into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes until puffed and bubbly around the edges.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: quick & easy salmon croquets
directions: Drain and debone salmon. Mix in egg, onion, flour, corn meal, and baking powder. Shape into balls and cook in hot oil until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°F.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saut onions in butter or bacon drippings. Put in deep baking dish in layers: onions, soup, cheese and croutons. Use for 2 layers. Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well. Add the rice and spinach.
Pour all into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with the melted butter and cheese.
Bake about 30 or 40 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat yolks. Add water and extract and blend.
Gradually add yolk mixture to chocolate mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: sausage pancake bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain excess fat.
Mix pancake mix, eggs, milk and oil together.
Add sausage.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with syrup.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add ingredients in order.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven until it is set.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar.
Cover.
Shake until sugars are dissolved.
Chill.
Shake again before serving over fresh or canned fruit salads or tossed greens.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: brown sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl until stiff peaks form. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, blending until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into flowerets.
In bowl combine broccoli, raisins, bacon, onions, kernels and cheese.
Set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli and cauliflower.
Peel onion and cut into strips.
Cut up broccoli and cauliflower into bite size chunks.
Toss broccoli, onion and cauliflower.
Add dressing and bacon bits to vegetables.
Toss together.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Combine eggs, butter, salt, sugar mixture, syrup, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°. Bake 50 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean from center.

title: honey mustard salmon fillets
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine mustard, honey, melted butter and curry powder to make sauce.
Put a small amount of sauce on bottom of greased baking pan.
Put in salmon skin side down.
Brush top with sauce.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn.
Baste with sauce generously. Continue to bake additional 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Fold in the milk, mini marshmallows and peanuts into the chocolate.
Pour into the buttered dish.
Refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix liquids and sugar.
Place in large percolator.
Put cloves and cinnamon in filter basket.
Heat.
Makes 30 cups.
You could probably use a crock-pot and put the cinnamon and cloves in a cheese cloth or tea holder.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in cranberries.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until thoroughly moistened.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix next 8 ingredients and pour over crust. Mix last 4 ingredients and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: fast and easy shrimp and rice
directions: Steam shrimp. Mix with rice and tomatoes in saucepan.
Warm and serve.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Drain grease.
Cook noodles; drain.
While cooking noodles, simmer tomatoes, soup, vegetables and cheese into meat mixture.
Combine noodles with hamburger and place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Good!

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate.
When hard, remove from cookie sheet and place in another container.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add milk, vanilla and butter, mixing until smooth.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Blend well and pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain thoroughly.
Make one cup of white sauce; add cheese.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Put alternate layers of broccoli and sauce in greased casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 375° oven
until it bubbles.

title: layered casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in order listed in large baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour or bake in crock-pot on low setting all day.

title: all purpose marinade
directions: Combine, excellent for steak, chicken or boneless pork.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost and drain potatoes.
Combine corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter; set aside.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, cheese, soup and sour cream.
Add potatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Top with corn flake mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder.
Put butter and milk in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over batter mix, beating well.
Add vanilla. (Makes a very thin batter.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (tube pan) for 35 minutes (sheet cake).
Remove from pan immediately.

title: dilly brussel sprouts
directions: 1. Cook brussel sprouts using directions on package. Drain.
2. Mix Italian dressing, dill weed, and green onions or chives.
3. Pour over warm sprouts and chill several hours before
serving.

title: hominy dish ... for those who don't even like hominy!
directions: Drain all juice from cans.
Mix everything together.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbling.
Can make day before too. Potluck really likes this dish.

title: kay's vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix with mixer on medium.
Add nuts or raisins.
Bake in greased and sugared loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 3 loaves.

title: six flavored pound cake
directions: Let butter and margarine be room temperature. Cream sugar, margarine, butter and Crisco oil. Add eggs one at a time. Fold in flour and baking powder. Add milk and flavors. Beat 5 minutes.

title: kolbassi rolls
directions: Follow directions on roll mix package.
Roll up with kolbassi and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir in enough flour to right consistency.
Roll out in small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sweet and hot mustard
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Cook in top of double boiler stirring until thick.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Yields about 20 ounces.
Good on any sandwich.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: egg and sausage loaf
directions: Cube the bread and place in a large loaf cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Brown sausage in frying pan and drain.
Place a layer of sausage (cooked and drained) on top of bread cubes, then add a layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix the eggs and milk (beat) and pour on top of the cheese.
Leave all night in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all together.
Be sure to crumble graham crackers.
Put in fridge and let set.

title: artichoke hearts stuffed with crabmeat and bleu cheese
directions: Mix hot sauce, worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayo, eggs, dry mustard, white wine and black pepper together.
Cut crusts of bread off and cut into little squares. Add to mixture and let stand while checking crabmeat for shells.
Add bleu cheese and heavy cream and mix together.
Now add crabmeat and stuff mixture into artichoke hearts.
Top with lemon, butter and white wine. Bake at 450° for 15-20 minutes or until crabmeat browns.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla for 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Beat in dry ingredients. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of morsels and the optional pecans.
Spoon into greased 9 x 4 loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables, bread and cheese.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in melted butter and milk.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop in food processor.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Use skillet the size of a dinner plate.
Brown potatoes in well-greased skillet.
When potatoes are done, add ham.
Combine eggs, Bisquick and milk; mix until smooth batter (consistency of pancake batter).
Add cheese.
Pour over potatoes and ham; cover and cook approximately 15 minutes or until batter rises, using medium heat.
Lay dinner plate upside-down in skillet and flip everything over onto plate.
This is done by gripping skillet handle with one hand and placing other hand on plate.
Flip quickly, then slice it back into skillet to finish cooking, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apple.
Add sugar and put in refrigerator overnight.
Add 1 cup of marshmallows and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Fold all ingredients into 1 pint whipping cream (whipped).

title: dutch cake
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk and butter.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle top of cake with cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar mixture while cake is still hot.

title: cheese omelet(serves 1)
directions: Pour egg into a preheated nonstick frying pan coated with cooking spray.
Cook until slightly firm.
Combine cottage cheese and seasonings and spread over half of egg.
Fold egg in half. Cover skillet and cook for 3 minutes.

title: lime chiffon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, sweetener, salt, lime juice and lemon rind in top of double boiler.
Cook and beat with rotary beater until thick.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot mixture; cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into lime mixture and mix well.
Pour into chilled rice cereal crust and chill until firm.
When ready to serve, add whipped topping if desired.

title: mustardy fried chicken
directions: Dry chicken with paper towel.
Salt and pepper.
In bowl, beat egg and mustard.
In separate bowl, combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in egg then roll in cheese mixture.
Saute in heated oil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add green pepper during last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, place layer of crackers.
In a bowl, mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat until thickens.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Place half of pudding on top of crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and remaining pudding.
Add another layer of crackers.
Mix frosting with 3 teaspoons of milk.
Spread on top of crackers.
Refrigerate for 6 to 10 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the 2 cans of corn in a baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients, using only half of cheese.
Stir well and put other half of cheese on top.
Cook, uncovered, in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sinfully good cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, mix sugar and undrained pineapple. Heat until sugar is dissolved.
After removing cake from oven, poke holes in it.
Pour hot pineapple mixture over hot cake and cool.
Prepare pudding as directed on package and spread on cake. Spread whipped topping over pudding and sprinkle with coconut and/or nuts.

title: spanish rice made easy
directions: Rice can be the long cooking rice or Minute rice in whatever amount you need for the occasion.
Being a working woman, I personally prefer the Minute type.
Either is equally good for this recipe.
Add the desired amount of picante sauce to the hot rice and voile!!
Spanish rice made easy, real easy.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Mix separately milk and pudding.
Add cream cheese mixture and Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies in blender or food processor.
Layer cookies and cream mixture.
Save lots of cookies for top.

title: puffy fried bread sopaipillas
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in Crisco; add milk to make a soft dough barely firm enough to roll.
Cover bowl and let stand 30 minutes.
Then roll out dough on lightly floured surface to about 3/8-inch.
Cut into diamond shaped pieces or 2-inch square pieces.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Turn to get evenly brown.
Drain on paper towel.
May be served with honey, butter, jelly, etc.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen pieces.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cover again with boiling water. Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, seasonings and vinegar. Cook for 15 minutes.
Pack into hot jars; seal at once.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Add all ingredients and congeal.

title: ambrosia cheese pie
directions: In
large
bowl,
beat	cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: chuck wagon chow
directions: Sprinkle beef
with
chili
powder,
salt
and	pepper. Brown slowly with
garlic
in salad oil in large skillet.
Add onions and green
peppers;
cook
slowly over low heat 10 minutes.
Drain beans
and
corn;	add
liquid
to meat mixture; cover.
Simmer 45	minutes or until meat is tender.
Add beans and corn; cover and cook 15 minutes longer or until vegetables are heated through.

title: mandarin green salad
directions: Toss slivered almonds in about 1 tablespoon sugar over low heat in frying pan.
Stir until caramelized.
Break salad greens into salad bowl.
Add celery, green onions and mandarin oranges. Toss with oil, cider vinegar and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Enjoy!

title: green pepper jelly
directions: In a large saucepan, combine green peppers, jalapeno peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring to prevent boiling over.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin, mixing well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off white film which forms on top.
Mix in food coloring.
Strain if you prefer a clear jelly. Pour into 6 (8 ounce) hot sterilized jars.
Cool on racks.

title: gnocchi
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Then put on a board and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Then cut small pieces from each strip.
Make indentations with 2 fingers to shape gnocchi.

title: cherry jello
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate until set.

title: bean taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in large skillet.
Drain excess liquid.
Add beans, taco seasoning, corn and salsa to meat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Transfer mixture to 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle on cheese and chips.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Combine paste and sauce in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add salt and pepper.
Slice and dice garlic, onion and mushrooms. Saute garlic in butter until golden brown; mix with sauce/paste. Heat until it bubbles.
Stir.
Saute onions in butter until limp; add to pot and stir.
Saute mushrooms until limp; add to pot and stir.
Reduce to simmer.
Simmer for 3 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.
After 2 1/2 hours, add sugar and blend.
Stir well. Sugar will blend flavors and kill the acid.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in a large shallow sheet pan.
Put in a very slow oven (250°) to keep warm and crisp.
Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Place on medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Continue to boil to the firm ball stage (248°) about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda; syrup will foam.
Take popped corn from oven and pour hot caramel mixture over it in a fine stream.
Stir to mix well.
Return to oven for 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes almost 2 pounds.

title: strufoli(honey clusters)
directions: Heat oil to 365° in deep fryer or deep saucepan.
In large bowl place flour and salt.
Make well in center of flour; add eggs, one at a time, mixing slightly after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix to make soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead.
Divide dough into halves.
Lightly roll each half 1/4 inch thick.
Use palm of hand to roll strips to pencil thickness. Cut into pieces about 1/4 to 1/2 inch long.
Fry only as many pieces of dough as will float, uncrowded, one layer deep in fat. Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned, turning occasionally during fry time.
Drain on paper towels.
Meanwhile cook honey in skillet over low heat about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add deep fried pieces, stirring constantly until all are coated with honey.
Remove strufoli with a slotted spoon and set in refrigerator to chill slightly.
Remove to a large serving platter and arrange in a cone shaped mound.
Sprinkle with multi-colored jimmies.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: company stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Dredge in flour.
Brown with onions in butter. Add seasonings and water. Cover and simmer gently until almost tender, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add soup and mushrooms; stir to mix.
Cook gently until beef is tender, about 30 minutes. At serving time, heat mixture piping hot and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 10.

title: spaghetti with meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato paste, in large pot and bring to medium boil for 20 minutes stirring every 5 minutes. After 20 minutes reduce to low simmer for 2 hours.
Then add two cans of tomato paste, plus two cans of hot water.
Then start meatballs.

title: blueberry almond cake
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level with a knife.

title: hot vegetable salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute garlic in olive oil.
Discard garlic.
Add bouillon and spices and bring to a boil.
Combine vegetables in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over vegetables and toss.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir 4 to 5 times while baking.

title: smoothie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Then refrigerate for 1 hour.
This recipe will serve 2 people.

title: southern pumpkin pecan pie(from a long-time alabaman cook)
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and salt thoroughly together.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Top with pecans.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Grease a Pyrex pie dish with butter. Place jalapenos around the bottom of dish. Cover evenly with the cheese. Over this, place green onions, tops and all. Cover with eggs, beaten with pinch of salt and dash of garlic powder. Place in oven at 225° for 1
hour. Cut into pie wedges and serve hot.

title: valentine's day cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using an electric mixer, beat butter until fluffy.
Scrape bowl as needed.
Add granulated sugar and beat until combined.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and then flour, 1/3 cup cocoa powder and salt.
Scrape dough onto a piece of waxed paper; pat into a disc and cover with another piece of waxed paper.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Using a 2 1/2-inch heart-shaped cutter, cut out cookies; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until tops are firm and cookies are set around the edges, about 15 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes, then transfer the cookies to racks to cool completely.

title: diane's grandmother's one-half pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Slightly floured chopped pecans may be added to batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour or until done.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in center and add sour cream and milk.
Stir until dough clings together.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface 10 to 12 strokes.
Pat into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 10 or 12 biscuits.
Bake on ungreased pan 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix by hand together your margarine, powdered sugar and white sugar until creamed.
Add oil; mix together.
Add other ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut out.
(I pat out by hand.
Cookies are softer and thicker.)
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Frost.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test if done with straw.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrot, apple and onion in a bowl; toss gently. Set aside. Combine oil and next 4 ingredients, stirring well. Pour dressing over carrot mixture; toss gently just before serving. Yield: 4 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add hamburger or meatballs.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: patsy davis' strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Slowly add water and bring to a boil until mixture becomes clear.
Remove from heat and add cherry Jell-O, mixing well.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Stir in blueberries by hand.
Use paper liners.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix until creamy.
Shape into eggs.
Chill overnight, then dip into melted chocolate.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Take orange jello (dry) and cottage cheese and stir together. Add Cool Whip and cans of Mandarin oranges.
Stir all together. Refrigerate.

title: quick chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti using garlic salt or garlic powder to season instead of regular salt; rinse well.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel and halve peaches.
Cook brown sugar in 5 tablespoons butter in 10-inch ovenproof frying pan until dissolved.
Off the heat, arrange peach halves, cut side up, in pan.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Beat 8 tablespoons butter with granulated sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture by thirds, alternating with sour cream. Spread over peaches and bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
This takes a little work but is very much worth it!
I'm sure some substitutions can be made to reduce the calories and fat!

title: chocolate fruit krispies
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. Combine next three ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat for about 10 minutes or until melted.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix.

title: beef bulgogi
directions: Slice beef against the grain into 1/4-inch slices.
In bowl, stir together all other ingredients.
Add meat and toss until all pieces are covered.
Marinate at least 1 to 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in fridge.
Can barbecue, broil or saute. Serve with rice.
Use sauce on rice.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Cook and drain beef and onion.
Stir in drained green beans, soup, oregano, salt, sugar and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell. Place top crust over filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: emerald salad
directions: Melt jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water in a medium-large pot on stove.
Add marshmallows until they are melted.
Add pineapple juice.
Remove and put in refrigerator to chill slightly, then add whipping cream, pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Fold together.
Put in a mold and chill.

title: box oven cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch square pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine in the pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 400° box oven.

title: boston drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until smooth.
Blend in eggs and mix.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla extract.
Beat until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut the cherries into halves and place a half on each cookie.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on cookie racks.
Remove from cookie sheet to cookie rack.

title: heavenly potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes the night before with skins on for 30 minutes in salt water.
Peel and grate potatoes; add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cauliflower in salad bowl; add onion and cheese, mix together.
Sprinkle sugar over top; put in refrigerator.
Fry bacon, chop and drain.
Add Miracle Whip, toss; add bacon and serve.

title: squash relish
directions: Cover first 3 ingredients with ice water.
Add salt and let stand one hour.
Drain and rinse.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for approximately 2 hours.
Be sure all fruits are drained well.
You can use low calorie cottage cheese, if desired.

title: dixie peanut brittle
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Heat to a rolling boil.
Add peanuts.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook until syrup will spin a thread (or 293°).
Add butter, then soda; beat rapidly.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot and cook until a ball forms when dropped into a glass of water.
While cooking, stir constantly. When ball forms, take off stove and stir until it begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together. Store in a dry container. Mix with hot water as desired to taste.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until tender in salt water.
Drain.
Melt butter, onions and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add soup and cook until warm.
Add beans and pimento to mixture.
Pour into casserole.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: crunchy apple pie
directions: Mix 6 or 7 chopped apples with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and a dash of nutmeg or ginger.
Put in bottom of pie pan and dot with butter.

title: white trash snack mix
directions: In a very large bowl, mix all ingredients, except white chocolate. Melt white chocolate according to directions. Pour in white chocolate and mix well. Drop onto wax paper in heaps; should look like piles of trash.

title: apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and celery.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, salt, vinegar and celery seed.
Add to cabbage and celery mixture and toss together until well mixed.
Add apples and marshmallows. Toss again lightly. Walnuts may be added for extra flavor.
Top with paprika.
A delightfully different and tangy slaw.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix all together and spread in a layer in a baking dish.

title: chili dip
directions: Chop green chilies and onion.
Put all of the ingredients in blender and mix just enough to blend.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix crackers in mixer until broken.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press into greased sheet pan.
Melt 2 squares of chocolate and pour over chilled mixture.
Chill and cut.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients together, add to creamed ingredients and set in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
(May roll out dough and use cookie cutters.)

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce. Drain and flake crab meat.
Add to cream cheese mixture with 2 tablespoons minced green onion.
Turn into greased baking dish. Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: cherry over snow
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Line half of the pieces
in
a pan.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese. Blend
together,
then
add
container
of Cool Whip. Pour half of the mixture over broken angel food cake and half of
the cherries.
Then repeat over again.
Then with a spoon mash it down.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients and cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk together and pour over first ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: dilly panned summer squash
directions: Slice unpeeled squash to make 3 cups.
In medium skillet, melt butter.
Add squash; sprinkle squash with parsley, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium low heat 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: rhubarb orange jam
directions: Cut orange slices in small pieces.
Cook rhubarb, sugar and candy all together for about 8 minutes or until it jells from a spoon.
Most of the orange candy will be dissolved.
Put in jars and seal with paraffin.

title: ham filled party biscuits
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour until thoroughly mixed.
With hands, form into a ball, wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate for 1 hour, before rolling out.
Roll out dough into a rectangle, about 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle with ground ham.
Dust lightly with brown sugar.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut roll into 16 slices, place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: okra 'n rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, then crumble. Save 1/2 cup of bacon grease. Fry okra in grease until tender. Add onion, then add cooked rice and then crumbled bacon; heat well. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french onion soup(made in crock-pot)
directions: Pour bouillon or stock in crock-pot.
Cook onions in large skillet in butter; cover and let cook for 15 minutes.
Uncover and add salt, sugar, flour and vermouth.
Stir well.
Add to stock in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (3 hours on high). Top with grated cheese before serving.
Croutons may be added, if you wish.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Spread about 2/3 of crushed vanilla wafers on waxed paper or slick side of freezer paper.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small loaf shape in vanilla wafer crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over loaf as you roll into shape.
Wrap in wax paper and aluminum foil.
Chill.
Store wrapped in refrigerator.
Slice only as needed.

title: nondairy tofu sour cream
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Use as a replacement for sour cream.

title: raspberry streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Stir in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture; set aside. Press remaining crumbs onto bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread raspberry fruit evenly over baked crust to within 1/4-inch of edges.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup white chocolate chips.
Combine reserved crumb mixture with remaining 1/4 cup white chocolate chips and almonds.
Spread fruit mixture, pressing lightly into fruit.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely on wire rack and cut into squares and serve. Makes 16 servings.

title: apple maroon
directions: Fill pie pan with apples.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Beat egg; add 1/2 cup sugar, flour and margarine (melted).
Mix together and pour dough over apples. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Beat sugar, butter and peppermint flavoring until smooth. Spread on cake layers.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Spread on peppermint layer.
Sprinkle crushed candy cane on top. Refrigerate 15 minutes to set, then cut.

title: green tomato fritters
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and milk.
Sift flour and salt; add to milk mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Dip sliced green tomatoes into batter; drain off excess.
Fry in hot oil (375°) to depth of about 1 inch in skillet for about 4 minutes.
This makes about 1 cup batter and is good also to use for frying sliced squash or eggplant.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions; add salt and water.
Store in refrigerator for 48 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour mixture over salad and toss.

title: fluffy boiled icing
directions: Put in top of double boiler and cook over hot water, beating constantly with electric mixer until stiff enough to spread on cake.

title: haddock newburg casserole
directions: Place haddock fillets in buttered casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Tear 2 slices American cheese into strips; lay on top of haddock.
Cover with cream of shrimp soup.
Cover casserole dish and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(A combination of haddock with scallops or shrimp may be used.
Also, bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers can be added for a topping.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a large casserole dish.
Make a layer of sliced onion.
Put a layer of sliced potatoes, followed by another layer of onion.
Salt and pepper.
Make a layer of pork chops.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Spread the sauerkraut over the chops.
Pour the cup of milk around the edges of casserole; cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar in microwave-safe glass bowl.
Add cocoa; mix well. Place oleo and milk on top.
Do not stir.
Place in microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: georgia apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs and lemon juice.
Add flour, soda and salt; blend well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
A few minutes before cake is done, prepare topping.

title: special banana pudding
directions: Mix about 1/2 can milk with sugar and flour.
Then mix in egg yolks, then add the other 1/2 can milk.
Put in sweet milk and stir well.
Add vanilla.
Put all in double boiler.
Stir until thick.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Take off heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Stir until all blended, then stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pan and let cool.

title: frogmore stew(serves 8)
directions: In a very large pot, boil potatoes.
Slice sausage thin and fry until lightly brown (this does not have to be done, but it removes a lot of the grease from the sausage); add to pot with potatoes.
Add crab boil and corn-on-the-cob.
When the potatoes are almost done, boil together for about 10 minutes and then add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turn pink.
Serve with lots of napkins.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Mix pumpkin, oil and eggs. Add pumpkin mixture to dry ingredients and mix until smooth. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool, then frost.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain water off.
Melt butter in hot squash. Beat egg in milk and add to squash.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle top with 1/2 cup herb mix.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Heat oil in a deep skillet; saute onion and celery 5 minutes. Mix in pork, soy sauce and bean sprouts.
Add to the skillet, stirring steadily to the boiling point.
Cook 3 minutes longer. Serve with rice and chow mein noodles.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring 1/2
cup water to boil.
Add chopped broccoli and onion; cook
well.
Do
not drain.
Add soup, milk and cheese. Stir and cook until heated through.	Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet with butter or spray with Pam. Place on dough board or trivet.
In a heavy bottom pan, combine the water, sugar and Karo.
Cook over medium heat, stirring gently until mixture spins a thread.
Sprinkle in the peanuts; stir until the peanuts pop and the mixture turns an amber color.
Turn off heat.
Add salt and butter.
Mix well.
Add the soda.
Stir quickly.
Mixture will foam.
Pour immediately onto sheet.
Spread thin.
Thinness is what insures the candy will be brittle.
When cool, break in pieces.
Do not make on a rainy day.

title: 1, 2, 3 shrimp scampi
directions: Marinate shrimp in bowl for 20 minutes with cooking wine, oregano, garlic powder (save 1 tablespoon for topping), 2 tablespoons lemon, pepper and olive oil.
Place shrimp in single layer of broiler pan.
Sprinkle rest of garlic powder over the layer of shrimp.
Cover entire layer with bread crumbs.
Saturate with the remaining 2 tablespoons lemon and 2 to 3 sticks of melted butter.
Broil over low flame (400°) for approximately 15 minutes, keeping a careful eye on (do not overcook).
Serve with white or yellow rice.
Enjoy!

title: low range lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles per directions on package.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley together.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add evaporated milk, sage, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add beef, cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup of cheese and onion.
Blend well.
Form and put in pan.
Arrange bacon on top of loaf.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top; bake 10 minutes longer to melt cheese.

title: rice and hormel oven bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
large skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in raw vegetables and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring often.
Stir in Minute rice and continue cooking until rice is golden brown.
Stir frequently.
Reduce heat and add water.
Cook over low heat until most of the water is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
In a 3 or 4-quart baking dish, stir together cream of chicken soup, diced tomatoes and green chiles, salt and Hormel chunk breast of chicken.
Stir in rice/vegetable mixture until well mixed.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit pound cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let set overnight.
Combine the flour, cream of tartar, mace and salt.
Cream together 1/2 cup sugar, the butter and egg yolks.
Add the vanilla.
Beat the egg whites with 1 1/2 cups sugar until stiff.
Blend dry ingredients with the butter mixture.
Fold in egg whites, then fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased and floured 9-inch tube pans.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and cranberry sauce.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Add bananas and nuts.
Finish setting.

title: puppy chow mix
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine in microwave 3 minutes on half power. Pour over cereal and mix well. Put sugar in bag. Add cereal and shake until covered.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Rinse and pat dry.
Combine hot sauce and butter in a bowl.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Arrange wings in a single layer in baking dish; bake in a preheated 450° oven for 35 minutes or until well done and browned.

title: sugar-free impossible french apple pie
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Mix apples and spices in baking pan; sprinkle lightly with salt. Combine remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth. Pour over apples.
Melt oleo and pour over apples. Cover with streusel. Bake in 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: best ever corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, green pepper, red sweet pepper and salt in large plastic or glass container (do not use aluminum).
Cover with cracked ice. Let stand 3
hours, tightly covered.

title: baked ham
directions: Bake ham 2 hours, marinated with mixture, basting.
Bake until done and tender!

title: old time spoon rolls
directions: In this order mix together.
Drop in greased muffin pans. Let rise 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and dot with butter.
Moisten edges of under crust.
Adjust top crust in which 6 vents have been cut.
Trim edges and seal with fingers or foil.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skilligalee spoonbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside. In a large saucepan, heat butter and milk on high heat until mixture begins to boil; then turn off heat. Stirring rapidly, all at once add the cornmeal, sugar and salt. Continue beating while adding the beaten eggs all at once. Pour into prepared pan and bake in 350° oven until set and golden on top, about 25 minutes. Makes 10 servings.

title: wing-ding macaroni casserole
directions: Wash and drain a batch of firm green beans.
Remove ends and strings.
Use a large darning needle with heavy white thread and thread through the pod near the middle of each bean, pushing them along the thread so that they are about 1/4-inch apart.
Hang up strings of beans in a warm, well-ventilated place to dry.
They will shrivel and turn greenish gray.
Cover with warm water and soak overnight.
Drain, renew water and parboil slowly for a half hour.
Drain again.
Cook slowly with ham hock or salted pork until tender.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water 8 minutes or until tender. Drain well.
Place 1/2 of cauliflower in a 1-quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with half each of yogurt and cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining cauliflower, yogurt and cheese.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: In 2 pie pans, place 1/2 stick butter.
Melt butter in pans. Mix ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in each pan. Sprinkle small amount of nutmeg on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pear harlequin
directions: Combine pears, oranges and pineapple in bowl.
Weigh fruit. Add sugar equal to 2/3 of the weight of fruit.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Combine with cherries in saucepan.
Cook until pears are tender.
Spoon into hot sterilized 1-pint jars.
Seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.
Cool upside-down for 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: macaroni salad (2)
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, rinse and drain.
Add miracle whip (I add enough to cover well).
Add chopped green peppers, onions, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Fold in peas and cheese.	Make the night before, the flavor goes through more.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time. Make thick paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt together and add to creamed mixture. Add soda and vinegar; mix well.
Bake in a 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry jello dessert
directions: Bring pie filling, pineapple and water to boil.
Add jello. When partly set, add whipped cream and cheese.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in round or oblong 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spray vegetable spray oil on 9 x 13-inch pan and press one can crescent dough flat to cover bottom of pan.
Cream cheese with sugar.
Add yolk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well and spread over dough.
Top with other can of crescent rolls which have been spread out to fill pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: almond joys
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, coconut, milk, pecans and melted butter in a bowl; roll into little balls.
Melt chocolate and wax in boiler.
Take balls and stick a toothpick in the middle, then dip into chocolate.
Let set on waxed paper until it hardens.

title: christmas souffle
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. Gradually add the sugar, beating constantly. Mix the raisins and nuts together and fold into the egg whites. Pour mixture into buttered baking dish and set dish in pan of hot water. Bake in a moderately slow oven (325°) about 30 minutes. Serve at once.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Beat cold water and mayonnaise together.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch layer pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: margie's punch(yields 100 servings)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil to dissolve.
Combine with Jell-O and cool.
Add lemon juice and pineapple and freeze.
Set out 1 hour before serving.
Break up and pour about 3 bottles of ginger ale.
Stir.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Combine sugars, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl (try a large stockpot or kettle).
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until thoroughly blended.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 325° preheated oven about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 9 to 12 dozen.
These freeze well.

title: lindberg special(uncooked relish)
directions: Chop or grind all vegetables.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours. Press and drain all juice off.
Add white vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Do not seal, keep refrigerated in a gallon jar.
Keeps for months.

title: carrot cake(torta di carote)
directions: From my good friend, Joyce.

title: cheri's zucchini
directions: Combine ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted well.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Sift the
flour,
soda	and salt together. Cream butter and sugars until
light.
Add
egg and salad oil, mixing well. Stir in flour mixture, oats, flavoring, nuts and coconut.
Add Grape-Nuts last; mix well.

title: oriental chicken ramen salad
directions: Dissolve flavor package and sugar in oil and vinegar.
Break up uncooked noodles and add to marinade.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serves 5 as a main dish.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together for crust; pat out in 8 or 9-inch square dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Put in 12 x 18-inch dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Add chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in mushroom soup, milk and cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken and olives to spaghetti.
Place in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix and cut in the cheese.
Add water to combine; form into balls.
Bake at 350° until bottom is brown, about 10 minutes.

title: pork with sauerkraut
directions: Combine butter with sugar in a large saucepan.
Cook slowly over low heat, stir constantly, until sugar
is melted.
Add onion and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add gravy, sauerkraut, salt and caraway seed.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Add pork to sauerkraut and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with crescent rolls.
Brown sausage (scramble). Drain and pour over rolls. Add hash browns to cover. Beat the eggs with the milk.
Pour in pan. Top with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 325° until done.

title: scalloped pineapple(good with ham)
directions: Butter baking pan (8 x 10-inch).
Place drained pineapple in bottom.
Cover with cheese. Sprinkle flour mixed with sugar on top. Pour juice from pineapple over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans with beef
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add small onion while browning; drain.
Combine beef and all other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; add strips of bacon across the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients slowly (or steam) in fresh bacon grease.
When done, put in big container, but leave grease in skillet.
In the same skillet, put ground chuck and cook slowly. Sprinkle flour over meat to make thick.
While first mixture is steaming, in big pan pour the tomato soup, tomatoes (run through food processor and take fingers and mash) and tomato sauce.
Into this put the seasonings and sugar.
Cook spaghetti.
After cooked, wash with cold water and put everything in large pot.
Add olives, mushrooms and Mexicorn.
Pour into casserole dishes and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until thoroughly hot. This makes a lot.
Good for a crowd.

title: six minute pecan pie
directions: In large bowl stir together first five ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: holstein torte
directions: Put the rest of condensed milk into it.
Mix all together and pour over crust.
Freeze.
Makes 12 - 16 servings.

title: betsy's shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter.
Add chopped onions, garlic clove and green olives.
Cook 2 minutes in butter.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, bay leaf, thyme, chopped parsley or flakes, sugar, salt, red pepper, sliced mushrooms and chili sauce.
Cook about 1 hour in saucepan.
Sauce can be prepared day or so in advance.
Do not add shrimp until heating to serve.
Add 1 package frozen shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.
Do not add shrimp until just before serving time.

title: spicy sweet potato balls
directions: Mash the hot sweet potatoes; add brown sugar, butter, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add egg and continue mashing until thoroughly combined.
Chill if not firm.
Form mixture into balls, using 1/3 cup for each ball and placing 3 miniature marshmallows in the center of each ball, if desired.
Dredge balls in graham cracker crumbs.
Place in a baking pan and bake in a hot oven (400°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 8 sweet potato balls.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan and slowly mix remaining ingredients into melted butter. Heat thoroughly and stir.
DO NOT BOIL.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
They taste better when refrigerated.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Beat until creamy the first six ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with 6 ounce package Nestle's chocolate morsels.
Bake at 375° for 1 minute.
Then run knife through dough to marbleize. Bake 12 to 14 minutes more.
Makes 24 squares.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices; add to apples and mix.
Put in pie shell and dot with butter.
Adjust top crust; perforate with a knife and dot with butter.
Bake for 50 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.

title: three minute pastry shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 9-inch pie pan.
Combine oil and milk in measuring cup and whip with fork.
Pour all at once over the flour mixture.
Mix until mixture is completely damp.
Press into pan to form shell in uniform thickness.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Put all ingredients into pan, except sour cream and pie crust. Boil 1 minute. Chill, covered with plastic wrap, about 40 to 50 minutes or until cool. Fold in sour cream.
Put in crust and top with whipped topping or whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add the next four ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell; pour filling over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes longer.

title: potatoes with spinach
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy; add chives, dill and spinach.
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge icing
directions: Mix together the flour and vanilla in a bowl and set aside. Then mix together the sugar, cocoa and water. Cook on stove until it reaches the soft-ball stage. Next, add the flour mixture. Stir until mixed well together. Then pour on cake.

title: peppered salmon fillet with onion compote(from pierre franey)
directions: Cut fillets slightly on the bias into 4 square pieces.
Peel onions and chop into 1-inch cubes (about 5 1/2 cups).
Heat 2 tablespoons margarine in a heavy casserole dish; add onions. Cover and cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Onions will start to brown.
Uncover; add vinegar, clove and Tabasco.
Cook briefly until vinegar is almost evaporated.
Stir in honey and cover tightly.
Cook 10 minutes. Sprinkle salmon with salt.
Coat with oil and pepper.
Preheat charcoal grill or broiler.

title: heavenly delight pie
directions: Drain crushed pineapple.
Chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and divide mixture into 2 pie shells.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Thoroughly mix meat and seasonings.
Spoon meat mixture into a 5 1/2 cup ring mold. (I use a loaf pan.)
Firmly pat meat into mold.
Unmold meat mixture in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Spoon off the meat drippings and fat.
To glaze meat loaf, combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Carefully spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated pot roast of beef
directions: Combine all ingredients (except flour and water).
Cover and refrigerate the meat to marinate overnight.
Drain the marinade and save.
Brown meat in a little oil or butter.
Bring marinade to a boil, put meat into marinade and simmer slowly for approximately 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and thicken liquid using flour and water.
Blend flour and water and slowly add to marinade, using only enough of flour/water mixture to thicken.
Discard remainder.
This can be done in a crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours, also works nicely if cut into bite size pieces and done as a stew using vegetables to your liking.

title: mexican snack squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust. Firmly press perforations to seal. Bake for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. Spread beans over crust. In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread over beans. Sprinkle cheese, onions, tomatoes and olives evenly over sour cream mixture. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Cut into squares. Serve with salsa. Makes 48 appetizers.

title: pasta with asparagus
directions: In a skillet, cook garlic and Tabasco in oil and butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add asparagus, salt and pepper.
Saute asparagus until it's crisp-tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over hot pasta and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crock-pot dogs
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in pot and simmer on high until dissolved enough to put hot dogs into mixture.
Cook on high for one hour.
Cut down to low and serve when ready.

title: geneva's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: clam sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add other ingredients (except clams) and simmer 2 hours, then add clams and juice and simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Season to taste and enjoy.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients; beat in egg and yolk.
Add next 3 ingredients; add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and sugar.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge or chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, Carnation milk and syrup in pan.
Stir up well. Cook until rolling boil; reduce heat, stirring constantly or often.
Cook until forms soft-ball in cup of cold water. When soft-ball is formed remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir up and beat until ready to pour into buttered container.

title: stove top chicken
directions: Chop chicken into bite sizes.
Add celery soup and chopped, fresh celery.
Add 1/2 cup broth.
Cook on top of stove.
Add chopped onions on top of the chicken.
Cover.
Cook another 10 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let rise.
Roll out and sprinkle with a brown sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Roll up and cut in small slices.
Put in buttered pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° until brown.
May put on icing or eat as is.

title: broccoli rabe and curried chicken
directions: Steam rabe and coarsely chop. Keep warm.
Warm remaining ingredients for 10 minutes in frying pan. Serve on top of warm rabe.

title: boneless pork chops casserole
directions: Batter and fry boneless pork chops until golden brown.
Lay cooked pork chops in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish; cut raw potatoes.
Lay this on top of chops.
Cut raw onion; lay this on top of potatoes. Cut butter; lay this on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste, then fill dish with water to top of potatoes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour both soups on top; mix if needed.
Add more water if needed.
Cook for 30 minutes more.

title: shrimp ball with sauce
directions: Mix all together and form ball.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Stretch and pat rolls into 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan (or cookie sheet with sides).
Moisten lightly and smooth seams to join.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on pan.

title: golden gazpacho soup(serves 6)
directions: Heat the oil in a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add the red bell pepper, onion, apple and carrot.
Saute, stirring frequently, for 5 to 7 minutes or until the onions are translucent.

title: imperial crab
directions: Place minced peppers and butter in a tightly covered pan; steam for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs, salt, cornstarch and dry mustard together; when well blended, stir in cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir steamed vegetables into egg mixture.
Season to taste with pepper.
Add crab meat to sauce; place in shells and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Add onion and cook.
Drain.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Add rice to sausage.
Add soup.
Put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: catfish and slaw sandwiches
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, celery, bacon, mayonnaise, parsley, mustard and horseradish.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all and bake at 350 about 40 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in heavy cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 12 vanilla wafers, bananas and another layer of pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pineapple tidbits, almonds and water chestnuts.
