In second bowl, combine salt, onion, mayonnaise and American cheese.
Blend and spread into flat casserole; sprinkle 1 1/2 cups crumbled potato chips on top.
Bake 10 minutes in 450° oven.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: turkey enchilada casserole
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan over high heat, stir turkey, onion, garlic, oregano and cumin in oil until turkey is crumbly and no longer pink, about 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup enchilada sauce.
Add salt to taste.

title: aunt dottie's fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix equal parts of fresh lime juice or honey to make 1/3 cup, beaten together until homogenized.
Using a small nutmeg grater positioned over juice and honey, grate enough whole nutmeg to amount to 1/4 teaspoon.
Combine with juice and honey; drizzle over fruit.

title: orange mallow frost
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet; stir until dissolved.
Chill until almost firm; fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Fill 6 dessert dishes; chill until firm.
Garnish with additional marshmallows and orange sections, if desired.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken or turkey, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with fresh lettuce salad and bread.
This is low calorie and low-fat.

title: mouth-watering turkey stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms in cold water.
Remove stems and set aside. Chop onion, stems of mushrooms and celery fine and saute in 1/4 cup butter or margarine about 5 or 6 minutes.
Add sage and cook 1 minute.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Simmer in a large pan for about 20 minutes the potatoes, water, carrots, celery, onion, parsley flakes and bouillon cubes.
Add Velveeta cheese, cold milk and flour.

title: philly cheese steak sandwich
directions: Heat heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add some oil, then onions and peppers.
Cook stirring till caramelized.
Add seasonings, stirring for a bit.
Push to one side of skillet, add meat and cook till no longer pink.
Top with cheese and let melt.
Put on toasted french bread or hamburger buns and enjoy.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Lightly butter dish and set aside.
Mix cocoa and sugar together well.
Coat sides of a heavy sauce pan well with butter. Add sugar and cocoa, Karo, cream, or milk, and salt.
Cook while stirring to firm ball stage (small amount holds its shape when dropped in a cup of cold water).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until it starts to thicken and pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares, cool and serve.

title: grandmother's frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, apricots and pineapple.
Reserve juices. Place fruit in large bowl.
Add marshmallows and set aside. Place juices in saucepan and stir in gelatin.
Place over medium heat.
Heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool slightly. Pour over fruit.
Stir in diced cherries and cherry juice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Jiffy, until well mixed.
Add Jiffy mix.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave until done.
Cut a lengthwise slice from the top of each baked potato; discard skin from slice. Scoop out the insides and place in a large bowl.
Mash.
Add margarine.
Beat in enough milk to make stiff consistency.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add shredded cheese as desired. Pile mashed potato mixture back into potato shells.

title: easy chicken special
directions: Cook broccoli (but not fully) and arrange in baking dish. Place cooked chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry skillet pie
directions: *May substitute other fillings.

title: pesto (basil sauce)
directions: Put
basil, garlic and pine nuts into a blender.
Blend at low
speed
for
a
few
seconds until the ingredients are chopped.
Add
tablespoons cheese and half of the olive oil and blend
again.
Scrape
the mixture down from the sides of the blender.
Turn speed to low and trickle in remaining olive oil while blending.
By hand stir in salt and pepper.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Add eggs, milk, celery and green pepper.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes and mix.
Put into lightly greased and baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and chop with scissors.
Mix with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Salad needs no dressing. Flavor improves with standing.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add potatoes, chicken broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Place mixture in blender and puree potatoes.
Return to saucepan.
Add pepper and cream.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grate or chop 12
cups zucchini, onions and peppers and mix. Add salt and let
stand
hours
or overnight.
Rinse well with water then
drain
well.
Mix
other
ingredients in large kettle and cook until it starts to thicken.

title: easy crab bisque
directions: Combine the two soups, milk, cream and seafood seasoning. Heat slowly, stirring occasionally.
Add crabmeat; heat to just below the boiling point.
Add salt to taste.
Just before serving, top with chives.

title: sour cream macaroni bake
directions: Cook
macaroni; drain.
Stir in cottage cheese and sour cream; set
aside.
Brown
hamburger and onion; drain grease. Stir
in salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 to
10 minutes.
Spoon half of mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with
half
of
the grated cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pickle beans
directions: To each quart of beans, add 1 teaspoon salt.
If water is added, add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart of water.
Let set 10 to 14 days.

title: easter bread
directions: In a small bowl, combine the yeast, water, salt and 1 teaspoon of the sugar.
Set aside until foamy, about 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, stir 4 1/2 cups of the flour and the remaining 3/4 cup sugar with a whisk to combine.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.

title: chile con queso(chile with cheese)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain and add chili peppers, cheese and salsa.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with scoops of corn chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredient together well. Shape into 1/2 inch balls. Put on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 15 min.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all together and roll into 2 logs, then roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: fancy japanese rice
directions: Place rice in shallow pan.
Toast at 350° until light brown, stirring occasionally.
Saute onions in melted butter in saucepan until translucent.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice and almonds.
Cook over medium heat until hot but not boiling; add salt to taste.
Place rice in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour hot liquid over rice; sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Yields 8 servings.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Drink 2 ounces daily.

title: breakfast brunch dish
directions: Cook and crumble bacon or ham.
Grease well a 9 x 13-inch dish with bacon drippings.
Fill bottom of dish with bread (remove crust).
Sprinkle cheese on top of bread.
Spread crumbled bacon on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread, cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 250° oven 1 hour.
You can try 300° oven.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix until smooth.
Spread onto ham.
Roll long ways. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or longer.
Slice, then serve on Ritz crackers.

title: carrie's pizza
directions: Let the bread raise as if you were going to make bread. Just do what it says on the dough bag.
Then grease your hands well, also grease
cookie sheet or to 14 to 16-inch pizza pans well. Then
spread
the
dough
in
pan
until even, then add tomato sauce,
cheese
and
items
you like best (enough for 2 pizzas). Bake at
about 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Also,
bread
doughs
will
make
thin crust pizzas.

title: maple syrup muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together; bake about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in 9 x 13 dish.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (break up any lumps) on top.
Cut up butter into thin squares and place evenly over top.
Sprinkle top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs, together and put into baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot wings
directions: Defrost winglets. Deep fry; drain off oil. Pour some hot sauce in container with lid. Drop in wings and cover; shake until well covered.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese and spread on cooled cake.
Drain pineapple and spread on top of pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan surprise pie
directions: Add baking powder to egg whites and beat well.
Add sugar, pecans and flavorings.
Fold in crumbs.
Bake in two well-greased 10-inch pie pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: tamale casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook meat.
Drain grease.
Return to skillet and add all other ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole dish and cook in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until brown.

title: sausage horns
directions: Cut rolls into thirds.
Spread with mixture of cheese, sausage and bread crumbs.
Start at wide end of roll and roll up.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon in a small bowl.
Pour over sliced apples and fill a deep pie pan 3/4 full.
Combine the flour, margarine, 2 cups sugar, egg and pinch of salt.
Pour over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Stir into large bowl in order given.
When well mixed, pour into large prepared loaf pan 3/4 full.
Rises handsomely; sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar in iron skillet, stirring constantly until it forms a syrup.
Remove from stove.
Stir in peanuts that have been heated.
Add butter and soda.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet to cool.

title: boiled icing
directions: Boil to soft ball stage.
Pour syrup over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until stiff enough to spread.

title: oven smoked trout
directions: Let fish soak, covered, for 24 hours.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours on each side (less time if fish are small).

title: e z fudge
directions: Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Spoon into a square pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli, southern style
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil in saucepan until onion is soft. Blend in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Heat until bubbly. Add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Blend in anchovies, olives and cheese.
Pour sauce over hot broccoli. Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over chopped cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add carrots and pepper.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Package in moisture vapor-proof material.
Freeze.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add grated cheese and mix until well blended.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap and chill for 24 hours.

title: mike's favorite oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Add margarine; cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Add brown sugar, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry dumpling pie
directions: Empty pie filling in saucepan, add sugar, oleo and water. Stir until well dissolved; bring to boil. Drop dumplings into fruit mixture. Cook until dumplings are done. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat the water; add salt and bring to a boil.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Make a white sauce and thin it with water.
Mix the Cheddar cheese, white sauce and the mustard.
Mix evenly with the macaroni and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with tomato paste, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: bacon-cheese potato skins
directions: Deep fry skins for about 45 seconds. Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler just long enough for cheese to melt.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon, green onions and sour cream
Serve along with soup.

title: cantonese style spareribs
directions: Place ribs, meaty side down, in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in very hot oven (450°) for 30 minutes.
Remove meat from oven; drain excess fat from ribs.
Turn ribs meaty side up.
Lower oven temperature to 350°; continue roasting for 1 hour.
Pour orange sauce over ribs; roast 30 minutes longer or until tender, basting ribs occasionally with the sauce.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and diced onion; drain. Add chili powder and simmer. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer: tortillas, meat, beans and Velveeta in that order twice. Cover with tortillas. Mix soup and tomatoes in small bowl. Pour over top of casserole. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: honolulu cooler
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Combine with juices and tea.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 6 generous servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in oven until brown on top, about 400° to 450°.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Mix all together (except cheese).
Put into baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: In large Dutch oven cook brisket, uncovered, in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat and cover. Reduce oven temperature to 300° and cook until tender.
Remove meat from sauce.
Refrigerate both overnight or at least several hours.
Slice meat paper thin.
Lay
slices in a flat pan.
Cover with sauce.
Heat in 300° oven for a little while.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer as follows in a clear bowl:

title: strawberries and double cream
directions: Hull and rinse strawberries; refrigerate.
Combine whipping cream and sugar in bowl.
Whip contents until they double in volume.
Add Cointreau to cream and blend.
Place 6 berries in small bowl and pour 1/2 cup of cream over berries.
Serves 4.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in the oil until soft.
Add ground beef and seasonings, stirring until meat loses its pink color.
Stir in the cooked rice, tomato sauce, ketchup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 - one cup servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow pkg. directions to make the cake.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix into cake pan and bake for 18 minutes.

title: potato salad for 100
directions: Cook eggs, clean and refrigerate.
Cook potatoes, drain and cool.
Dice onion and celery as desired.
Add onion and celery to diced potatoes.
Dice eggs and add to mixture.
Add relish.
Mix well.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and lettuce; tear lettuce into bite size pieces and cut cauliflower flowerets into bite size pieces.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon in large bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: party snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 6 cups mix.

title: grandma's vegetable beef soup
directions: Cover beef shanks, celery and onions in water; simmer in covered kettle.
Cool.
Cut up and trim meat.
Remove fat from top of stock.
Dice vegetables and add to broth; simmer (do not overcook).
Meat will cook too much if added too soon.
Add spices to taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients and bring to a boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into square cake pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix dressing, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings in a bowl.
Add salmon and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Pan-fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: no bake cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Spread on cherries.

title: pork chop bake
directions: In large skillet, brown 6 pork chops.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Saute onion and celery in drippings.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chops on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic (crushed); drain.
Mix remaining in soup pot.
Add hamburger mixture and simmer until celery is tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine apples, oranges and cranberries in a food processor or blender.
Add salt and sugar; mix well.
Mix salad dressing and cream cheese until fluffy.
Spoon into other mixture.
Add nuts. Mix jello with 1/2 cup hot water and cool.
Put all ingredients in jello and pour into oblong pan.
(Make the day before use.)

title: texas potatoes
directions: Spray one 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Mix first 6 ingredients. Spread in pan.
Mix next 2 ingredients. Spread on top of first mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut-peach upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a cake pan combine sugar, coconut and melted butter.
Pat evenly in bottom of pan.
Drain and arrange peach slices over coconut mixture.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Spread carefully over peaches.
Bake until done, about 40 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes in pan.
Invert on plate to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients with ground meat.
Add the oil so that the meat will not lose its juice and will become compact.
Put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain.
Add butter, then mix eggs, milk, salt and spice and cheese.
Pour into dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Add parsley and chicken to white sauce and heat.
Beat egg yolk, add milk and pour into chicken mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve in ring of rice, mashed potatoes or over toast.
Mushrooms or chopped eggs, chopped pimentos or olives may be added.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, then drain grease.
Mix kidney beans, spaghetti and catsup.
Mix together with beef and onion. Put in casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Add milk, egg and margarine and stir until smooth.
Fry in skillet or griddle until brown on each side.
Yields 20 to 21 medium size pancakes.

title: diabetic green bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread the mixture of cheese, mayonnaise and dressing on top of crust.
Sprinkle broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, etc. on top.
Any vegetables you choose can be used.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: In a small saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cook according to directions.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook beaten egg in butter.
Add chopped onion and the rice. Saute, stirring, over medium heat, until the mixture is slightly brown.
Mix 1/4 cup water with soy sauce and stir into the rice. Makes four servings.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Note:
Stir or shake seed in a frying pan over medium heat until golden.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Grease two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
In a large bowl, combine flour mixture with yeast from foil packet from roll mix, 1/3 cup wheat germ and sugar; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup water, sweet potato, margarine and 1 egg until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
With greased or floured hands, shape dough into a ball.
Knead dough for 5 minutes, until smooth, sprinkling with additional flour, if necessary.
Cover with a large bowl; rest 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 16 equal pieces.
Shape each into a ball, pulling edges under to make top smooth.
Place 8 balls each in each greased pan.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in a warm place (80° to 85°) until light and doubled in size (about 30 minutes).
Heat oven to 375°; uncover dough.
Beat remaining egg and 1 tablespoon water; brush over rolls.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon wheat germ.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; remove from pans, on wire racks.

title: spinach casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, 2 tablespoons of cheese, nutmeg and pepper.
Stir well.
Place in dish; sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350° until set.

title: frozen rum
directions: Mix in a gallon jug.
Store in deep freeze at least a day.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and butter; pack firmly in bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Spread on sandwich bread and serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water until tender.
Take chicken from broth, reserving 1/2 cup of broth.
Remove skin, debone and cut meat into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: green bean casserole(a good vegetable dish for buffets)
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter and flour; cook gently.
Remove from heat; stir in seasonings and cream.
Fold in beans.
Place in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese, then with crushed corn flakes mixed with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in a large saucepan.
Add tomato paste, mushrooms, garlic and spices. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Place 1/3 of sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crisscross layer of half the noodles. Spread with cottage cheese over noodles.
Add 1/2 of remaining sauce.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining noodles with 1 cup Ricotta cheese, remaining sauce, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour this mixture over Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Lightly stir. Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Cook
ground
chuck,
Worcestershire
sauce,
onion and pepper.
Drain.
Mix
together with other ingredients and pour into
crock-pot.
Cook
on High for 1 1/2 hours or bake in the oven at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy baked or grilled fish
directions: Marinate fish in dressing for 30 minutes.
Then put on grill or bake until white and flakes easily with fork.
Do not overcook.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in
warm
water
and	set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients in large
bowl.
Make
a
well	and
pour
in oil, buttermilk and
yeast mixture.
Beat by hand.
Mixture will be sticky.
Grease lightly and set in refrigerator for at least 3 to 4 hours.
Bake as needed.
Will keep for 3 to 4 days.
Make into balls or rolls and grease top.
Turn over in pan and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: kool-aid sherbet(for kids)
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in milk.
Pour into freezer tray. Freeze until mushy; spoon into mixer bowl and beat until smooth. Return to freezer tray.
Freeze about 2 hours.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Make ahead to let flavors blend.
This is good on most fresh fruits.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts and place in bottom of casserole dish. (You may leave them whole or cut into pieces.)
Mix together the soup, sour cream, onion and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter and put crushed crackers in butter and mix.
Place on top of casserole.
Cook in oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Empty pudding package into a large bowl.
Add pineapple tidbits slowly, a little at a time, with juice.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Stir in Cool Whip, a little at a time.
You can use less than 8 ounces, if you want a little smaller serving size. Mix in nuts, saving a few to decorate the top of the Cool Whip when mixing is complete.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: baby food cake
directions: Use electric mixer and mix all of the ingredients except the pecans until well blended.
Add the pecans, if wanted.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Mix in beans and tomato soup.
Put in 8 x 8 pan.
Put mashed potatoes on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: olive hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together everything but olives.
Wrap dough around large pitted green olives with pimento.
Set on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake on lowest oven shelf at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Pour mayonnaise mixture over all and stir.

title: karo crunch
directions: Combine popcorn, pecans and almonds on a cookie sheet, mixing well. Combine sugar, butter and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes or until it turns caramel color. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Mix to coat well.
Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: no-bake chocolate cheesecake(makes one 9-inch cheesecake)
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
In small saucepan, soften gelatin in water.
Over low heat, dissolve gelatin completely; set aside. In large mixer bowl, beat cheese and chocolate until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble; drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Mix milk, cereal and brown sugar together and let set for 5 minutes.
Measure and mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Add egg and flour mixture to cereal-milk mixture, then add grated apples.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: banana punch
directions: Cook sugar and water until dissolved.
Cool and add lemon juice to bananas and crush in blender, then add pineapple juice and ginger ale.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook oil and onions together until onions are transparent. Add all other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 2 hours.
Partially cover.
Put in jar and seal.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Cook bacon until almost crisp.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts.
Hold in place with a toothpick.
Place in a 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over water chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken breasts(serves 8)
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup with wine or milk.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Top each breast with a cheese slice; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: symphony of potato leek soup
directions: Combine chopped leeks, onion, celery, carrots and garlic (food processor is good for this) to melted margarine and cook until limp in a heavy soup pot for about 20 minutes.
Peel and cut potatoes in about 1-inch pieces.
Add potatoes and chicken broth to cooked vegetables.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Blend soup in blender or food processor.
Return to soup pot; add half and half and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Warm on low heat about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on pork chops and lay in baking dish. Put 1 tablespoon of brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of catsup on each pork chop.
Put 1 slice onion and 1 lemon slice on each pork chop.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello.
Add oil and water, mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Then add orange juice.
Do not use electric mixer; mix by hand.
Put in tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: quick veal parmigiana
directions: Brown meat in hot oil in a large skillet until golden on both sides.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breast with artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Flour chicken breasts.
Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Fry breast halves for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, artichokes and wine. Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Serve with rice.

title: cucumber snack
directions: One to 2 hours ahead, mix dressing packet with cream cheese and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Spread on party rye.
Top each slice with 1 slice of cucumber.
Shake dill weed on top.
Chill and enjoy!

title: cranberry delight
directions: In basket, place 1 teaspoon whole cloves, a little salt, cinnamon stick and brown sugar.
Boil sugar and spices in juice and water.
Serve hot!

title: praline grahams
directions: Bring oleo and brown sugar to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes and add chopped nuts.
Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Pour hot mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Let cool and break into separate crackers again.

title: aunt mary's coconut pie
directions: Mix above ingredients together
and pour into pie crust. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: italian squash
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add squash, celery, onion and garlic.
Mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add Red Sauce and rest of ingredients.
Mix, cover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans until crumb like. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13 pan and bake until golden brown at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: mud-snow-fire cake(also known as paul newman's favorite cake)
directions: *Put in freezer bag and break with the flat side of meat tenderizer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything together except the rice.
Place rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour soup-chicken-broccoli mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease (or spray with Pam) a large 14 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch pan or 2 smaller pans.
Brown beef and drain.
Boil the spaghetti in the box according to package directions.
Layer in order, beef, spaghetti, combine jar of sauce and mix sauce.
In bowl, empty soup and mix until smooth (don't add water).
Spread over spaghetti sauce.
Top with cheese.

title: italian bread
directions: In small bowl, mix garlic, oil, salt and pepper. With pastry brush, spread on to Italian bread; cut lengthwise and place on foil-lined baking sheet. Sprinkle each with onion, tomato and cheeses. Bake 5 to 6 minutes in 500° oven until cheese melts and crust turns brown.

title: sweet potato fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk, sweet potatoes and spices.

Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 234° on candy thermometer, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels.
Add marshmallow creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour quickly into 13 x 9 pan, spreading evenly.
Cool, cut in squares and store tightly wrapped in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bring chicken to a gentle boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Drain and dice up.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out flat on a pizza pan, pinching seams together.
Bake according to directions; cool.
Mix Hellmann's mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Spread on rolls. Top with broccoli, cauliflower, shredded carrots and pepperoni, then top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: chili
directions: Put hamburger in pan and cover with water.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add water if boils dry.
Add other ingredients and boil at medium heat for 30 minutes or cook down to sauce.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: In small bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
With fork, blend in flour until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: frozen pudding witches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter; stir until smooth. Slowly add pudding mix and beat at low speed until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Spread filling 1/2-inch thick on 12 graham crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Wrap with wax paper and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.

title: graham cracker nuggets
directions: Place graham crackers on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Boil brown sugar and margarine together about 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped (finely) pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dilly cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, cheese and sugar
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to cheese mixture, stirring until blended.
Beat slightly to remove lumps.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done. Serve warm.

title: cream soup base
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 3 cups of mix which equals 9 cans soup.
Store in fruit jar in cabinet.
To reconstitute, use 1/3 cup mix to 1 1/4 cups water (equals 1 can cream soup).
Stir over low heat until thick.
Add celery, broccoli or mushrooms as desired for specific type of cream soup.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal and flour.
Add onion and egg; stir.
Add buttermilk.
Shape into small balls and fry in deep fryer until brown.

title: banana split salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the milk and whipped topping until well blended. Fold in pie filling, bananas, pineapple and nuts. Chill at least 1 hr. before serving.

title: low calorie chili
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon fusilli
directions: Cook pasta and broccoli 10 to 12 minutes and drain. Add drained salmon.
In pan, melt margarine.
Make white sauce, adding bouillon and tarragon. Cook until bubbly. Cook 1 minute more. Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice. Spoon sauce over pasta. Sprinkle with parsley and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 312 calories per serving.

title: aunt jackie's milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Ways first, then mix all other ingredients together with melted Milky Ways.
Pour into ice cream freezer. Fill freezer remainder of the way with milk.
Make as you would homemade ice cream.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix salt, white and black pepper, thyme, basil and parsley with vegetable oil. Coat chicken breasts with the seasoned oil; mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach to thaw and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours. Roll into balls.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: pineapple carrot cupcakes
directions: Turn pineapple into wire strainer and drain; save the syrup. Turn carrots into wire strainer; press out excess liquid.
Resift flour with spices, soda and salt.
Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in half the flour mix.
Add pineapple and carrots, then remaining flour.
Fold in coconut.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add milk, banana and vanilla.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center for doneness.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Cook potatoes in a large amount of water until tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving 2 cups cool potato water. Add yeast, sugar, salt, flour and potatoes. Mix well. Cover and let stand in warm place for 3 days, stirring each day.
Leftover starter may be kept in refrigerator for later use.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine
first	3 ingredients.	Add next three ingredients and beat
well.
Combine
dry	ingredients
with rest of mixture and pour in 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: classic banana cream pie
directions: In a large saucepan, mix together the sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gradually stir hot mixture into eggs.
Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook over very low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.
Peel and slice 2 bananas.
Place in pie shell. Cover with filling.
Chill several hours.
Just before serving, peel remaining 2 bananas, cut in slices and place on top of pie.

title: skillet italian zucchini
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add zucchini and onion.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently until crisp-tender (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: eskimo creme dream
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with melted butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream, enough to spread.
Spread on frozen crust.
Freeze until solid.
Spread with fudge sauce. Return to freezer until sauce is frozen.
Spread with whipped cream and garnish with nuts.
Store in freezer.

title: green pea salad
directions: Prepare in 8 or 9 inch casserole dish.
Layer lettuce, pepper, celery, and onion.
Sprinkle on brown sugar; add peas. Spread on mayonnaise.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours before serving.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, margarine and Karo syrup to a boil over medium heat.
Cook approximately 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in nuts and pour on buttered platter.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Add mayonnaise, cheese, lime or lemon juice and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Turn into bowl.
Sprinkle top with paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through and top is a golden color.
Serve with Fritos corn chips.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook until golden brown.
Add broth and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients and let cool. Then blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: hash brown potatoes(baked dish)
directions: Mix in order given. Put in 4-quart casserole dish. Top with crushed cornflakes and melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids and eggs except margarine and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla after thickening.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add Cool Whip or meringue for topping.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in the order listed in a 2-quart bowl. Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and chill 8 hours.

title: easy donuts
directions: Add about 3 to 4 inches of grease in a skillet (hot).
Take biscuits and cut the center out (either with knife or biscuit cutter).
Drop biscuits into hot grease until golden brown. Remove and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Cut cabbage; add with rest of ingredients. Cook until cabbage is done.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine soups, milk, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes in an oblong 2-quart casserole dish.
Add a layer of ham, then spread half of soup mixture over this.
Repeat layers until all has been used.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and finish baking about another 15 minutes, or until potatoes are done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pack well the graham crackers and melted oleo.
Mix together for 10 minutes the 10x sugar, eggs and oleo.
Slice bananas over crust.
Pour in cream mixture.
Add drained pineapple over cream mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Add cherries and nuts as you would on a sundae.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.

title: homemade microwave brownies
directions: Place margarine and chocolate in a 2-quart glass batter bowl. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate is melted. Using a wooden spoon, beat sugar into chocolate mixture.
Add eggs to mixture; beat well.
Stir in flour and baking powder until well-combined.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.

title: seafood chowder(low-fat)
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add oil; place over medium high heat until hot. Add onion and next 3 ingredients; cook until tender.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Gradually stir in chicken broth, water and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring often, for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk, corn and hot sauce; return to a boil.
Add reserved shrimp and crab meat.
Cook 5 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink, stirring constantly.
Remove and discard bay leaves.

title: karen's recital punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; set aside to cool.
Put bananas, strawberries, pineapple juice, orange juice and water in a blender (a few at a time) and blend.
In a large bowl, put blended ingredients in with cooled sugar water.
Place bowl in freezer. Punch may be frozen days ahead.
Take punch out one hour before serving time.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 standard loaf pans.
In large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, pecans, baking powder and salt.

title: white fudge frosting
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar
and milk.
Stir until blended. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Boil one minute.
Cool. Gradually add powdered sugar until thick enough to spread; add vanilla.
If
frosting gets too hard,
add
a
few
drops
of Carnation milk.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello together in a large bowl.
Add oil and beat in eggs one at a time.
Add water and mix well.
Add strawberries and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 50 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°. Frost with Strawberry Frosting.

title: mustard glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush mixture on ham frequently during the last hour of baking.
Makes 1 cup (enough for 10 to 15 pound ham).

title: lemon-lime molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O's in boiling water; cool until slightly jelled.
Add rest of ingredients, mix well, pour into a mold and refrigerate.
This makes a large salad.

title: guacamole
directions: Grind all ingredients, except onion.
Stir in onion.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and meat.
Mix other ingredients with scalded milk and add to meat mixture.
Press into loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Pour into greased casserole dish and dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: heavenly hash(5 cup salad)
directions: Mix together and let sit at least 8 hours for best taste.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream 2 Tbsp. butter and sugar.
Add Graham cracker crumbs. Blend thoroughly.
Press in bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Brown the chicken wings in hot oil. Combine the remaining ingredients; add the wings. Simmer until liquid is reduced and wings are glazed.
Add mushrooms, if desired.

title: superb turkey casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine all ingredients, reserving 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: orange bisque
directions: Mix orange gelatin, sugar and boiling water until gelatin dissolves.
Chill until partially jelled, then whip.
Beat 1 can cold evaporated milk until stiff.
Add 2 teaspoons lemon juice. Fold the whipped gelatin and cream mixture together.
Pour into 13 x 8-inch dish line with graham cracker crumbs.
Cover with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill.

title: sara's easy tortilla soup
directions: In blender, combine undrained tomatoes, onion, garlic, cilantro and sugar. Blend until chunky. In a large pot, add vegetable mixture and chicken broth. Simmer 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel and slice cooked potatoes.
Pour Italian dressing over warm potatoes.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion and chopped eggs.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Fold into salad.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana lumpia
directions: Slice bananas lengthwise in half. Place 1/2 banana on a piece of lumpia wrapper. Sprinkle banana with cinnamon and sugar. Wrap banana in wrapper and use water to seal. Deep-fry. Cool and serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Combine sausage and cheese with remaining ingredients in crock-pot and heat on medium.
Turn down and serve with chips.

title: special sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan and add remaining ingredients. Makes about 1/3 cup sauce.
Pour over hot cooked vegetables (green beans, peas, asparagus, broccoli, green cabbage, cauliflower, etc.) or serve with artichokes.

title: 3-color pound cake(yellow, red and green)
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside. Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Add flavorings. Beat until smooth.
In each of two bowls (one for red and one for green), pour 1/3 batter.
Add 10 to 12 drops of food coloring to each bowl.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan. Pour in batter, alternating colors until all is in baking pan.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp; cut in small pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, catsup, lemon juice and horseradish.
Fold in shrimp. Chill at least 2 hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Spread pineapple on the bottom of pan (2 x 8 x 12-inch). Cover with cake mix.
Dribble melted oleo over cake mix (do not stir).
Add chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: orange filling
directions: Cook until thick and add lemon juice.

title: sunday spaghetti casserole
directions: Place butter in a cold skillet.
Add garlic; mash with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until butter is melted, then add meat and brown.
Add tomato sauce; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Place spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole; top with cream cheese mixture, then meat mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Mix cake mix, water and egg well.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup cake mix.
Press remainder into pan.

title: french cheese bread
directions: Melt cheese and butter together over boiling water.
When blended, stir in pimientos, chopped fine.
Slice loaf of bread in half, lengthwise, and spread with cheese mixture.
Place under broiler until cheese is brown and bubbly.
Slice to serve.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put hot milk into large bowl; add yeast, shortening, sugar & salt. Add flour, 1 cup at a time and knead until it pulls away from bowl. Let rise, work down. Put in pans, bake at 350 degrees 20-30 minutes depending on size of loaves.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine vinegar and next 7 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, then add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and meat. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes together.

title: lynn's homemade salsa
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Drain if too watery.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Drain pears; measure the pear juice and add water to make 1 3/4 cups.
Stir extract and syrup water into prepared jello.
Set 1 cup of jello aside.
Put all the rest into 1 1/2-quart dish or mold.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Quarter pears and place in jello.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Gradually blend jello mixture (the one cup you set aside) into cream cheese, a little at a time.
Pour over the chilled jello with pears.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: kiddie cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Fill ice cream cones to stem with mix.
Bake as directed for cupcakes.
When cooled, frost and serve.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cut pockets into one side of bread.
Cut sausage into pieces and stuff into pockets.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Dip bread slices into milk mixture, coating well on both sides.
Heat frying pan, using oil.
Fry bread until lightly browned on both sides.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serve with maple syrup and butter topping or fruit may be used for toppings.

title: perfect buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs first.
Then add ingredients in any order you want. Final batter should be smooth and creamy.
If you want to thin, add small amounts of regular milk (2% or low-fat is all right) and beat to desired consistency.
Oil and heat hot skillet to 350°. Place some batter in pan and flip when golden brown on bottom. Yields 12 to 15 (4-inch) pancakes.
Works best in non-Teflon electric frypan.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Use a rotating hand grinder to do cheese.
Chop pimento and pour juice over the ground cheese.
Add very little salt.
Add a generous amount of pepper.
Add Miracle Whip until very moist.

title: liver deluxe
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute onion.
Dredge slices of liver in flour and brown each side.
Pour gravy on liver and season with parsley, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 2 minutes and arrange on a serving platter.
Place bacon on top of liver.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil. Beat 3 minutes. Add pumpkin and dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: candy balls(coconut rum)
directions: Cream margarine and milk. Add rum and powdered sugar; mix well. Add nuts, fruit and coconut; mix well. Chill well about 2 hours. By hands, form small balls (3/4-inch). Keep hands coated with powdered sugar. Put balls on wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Melt chocolate. With toothpick, dip balls in chocolate; place on wax paper to dry. Melt white chocolate. Hand dip so topped with white chocolate (to cover toothpick marks). Chill and then package.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix Bisquick, flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Beat eggs slightly, reserve 1 tablespoon.
Stir remaining eggs and buttermilk into crumbly mix.
Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board.
Knead 20 times.
Shape into a ball.
Place into well-greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish. Cut 4-inch cross in center.
Brush dough with reserved egg.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from dish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Freeze before baking.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Can store in freezer for 2 or 3 months.

title: ben's barbecue cups
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, brown sugar and sauce.
Separate biscuits and place each one in an ungreased muffin cup; shape in cup.
Spoon meat mixture into each cup.
Put cheese on top of each one.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: pastor's spaghetti
directions: Cut onion and bell pepper to desired size; mix together in saucepan with chunks of link sausages.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil until tender.
Pour water off.
Lightly brown ground round. Add garlic powder and onion powder.
Let sausage simmer for 1 hour.
Boil water for spaghetti (see directions on box).
Add butter; drain spaghetti.
Mix together the spaghetti, sauce and meat mixture.
Add ketchup and oregano to taste.
Heat at low temperature, then serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove skin and debone; dice meat. Save broth.
Place rice in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup broth and diced chicken.
Pour a blended mixture of the 2 cans of soup and milk over the chicken.
Heat butter and 1/4 cup broth until butter melts.
Mix in the stuffing mix; spread evenly over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: leek carrot soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add carrots and leeks.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add chicken stock; bring to boil.
Add bouquet garni and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour.
Puree in blender.
Add cream before serving.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa sauce and seasoning.
Simmer and stir frequently for 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.
Line bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan with tortillas, overlapping edge.
Layer with 1/2 meat mix and 1/2 cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange remaining tortillas over top.
Then repeat layer of meat and cheese mix.
Spread with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all these ingredients together with a wire beater. Grease a large baking sheet (a cookie sheet with sides). Line the greased sheet with foil and grease foil. Pour batter in pan and bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes. Top will be dry. Sprinkle a towel (not terry) with powdered sugar and flip the cooked cake out on the towel. Peel off foil. Then roll cake and towel together while hot. Cool cake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: ruth's casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon, onion and salt.
Combine chicken, celery, almonds and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Cover with cheese and croutons.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey laced cookies
directions: Cream shortening, honey and sugar until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Stir in oats, coconut and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Dough will be crumbly. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 11 dozen.

title: oatmeal crisps cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well. Sift flour, salt and soda and add to batter.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin cream cheese roll-up
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add pumpkin; stir in dry ingredients.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Grease and flour the wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen cake onto damp towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and towel to cool completely.
Unroll and spread with cream cheese filling and re-roll; chill.

title: john wayne cheese canapes
directions: Combine cheeses and chilies, put into well-buttered jelly roll pan.
Beat egg whites and combine other ingredients.
Add to egg whites.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Remove from oven and spread chopped tomatoes over top; bake 30 minutes longer.
Test with knife that comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add sugar, salt, butter and syrup to eggs.
Fold in pecans. Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes, until set and pastry browned.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls (flat) on cookie sheet (according to directions on package).
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, dill weed and onion (salt and pepper to taste).
Spread mixture over baked crescent roll crust.
Top with fresh chopped veggies:
broccoli, green pepper, onion, tomato, zucchini and cucumber.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: pistachio pecan salad
directions: Empty contents of pudding in small bowl.
Add about 1/2 of Cool Whip; beat well.
Put in a large bowl.
Add pineapple and balance of Cool Whip.
Beat on low.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes (about 4) and prick several times with a fork: bake at 400 degrees for 1 hr. or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 min., stirring constantly.
Gradually add 6 c. milk; cook over med. heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 T. green onions, 1/2 c. bacon, and 1 c. cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated; stir in sour cream. Add extra milk, if necessary, for desired thickness.
Serve with remaining onion, bacon, and cheese.

title: peanut butter cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Combine other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat it.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into desired pieces.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into ovenproof dish that has at least 1 1/2-quart capacity.
Soften bread with small amount of milk.
Beat 4 tablespoons of sugar and egg yolks.
Add remaining milk; stir well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour milk mixture over bread.
Fold in raisins.
Dot with butter.
Place dish in pan of water.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until silver knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven.

title: farmer's chow
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and celery until brown.
Add beans, mushrooms, tomato sauce and bacon.
You can also throw in some brown sugar, molasses, part bottles of ketchup or chili sauce to taste.
We love to take this rib stickin' soup camping.
Serve with green salad and crusty bread.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine Bisquick and milk; stir with fork to a soft dough. Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Spread pork sausage thinly out to edge.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat egg yolks from the 2 eggs with the 1 whole egg and put in dry ingredients. Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff; sweeten.
Put on pie and brown lightly.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Put one can rolls in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread filling over this.
Put other can rolls over filling. Brush with egg white.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, broth, chilies and pepper.
Set aside. Soften tortillas by dipping one at a time into hot oil.
Drain tortillas on paper towel and stack.
Mix chicken and onion together.
Put approximately 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on center of tortillas.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and roll up. Place in shallow baking dish.
Continue until all tortillas are rolled.
Pour soup mixture over top and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: corn pie
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Mix rest with 1/2 cup melted butter and press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine 2 tablespoons butter, 1 cup milk, corn and salt.
Boil; reduce heat and cook 3 minutes.
Add flour to remaining 1/4 cup milk to form a smooth paste.
Add slowly to corn mixture.
Stir constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thick.
Cool slightly.
(Add onion salt, if desired.)
Add beaten eggs slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: veg-all casserole(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Melt margarine; mix with dressing mix.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental vegetable casserole
directions: Layer in 3-quart casserole the first 3 ingredients.
Dot with oleo.
Add in layers the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Top each breast with cheese slice; set aside.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until smooth; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with butter.
Bake chicken at 350° for 50 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: crock-pot meat balls in mushroom gravy
directions: Cut bread into very small pieces.
Combine meat, bread, salt, pepper and minced onion.
Using scoop or hands, shape into rounds about 1 1/2 to 2 inches.
Brown meatballs in hot skillet in small amount of oil.
Turn so all sides are browned.
Place in crock-pot.
Add soup and water.
Cook on low for 6 to 12 hours or on high 6 hours.

title: quick dessert
directions: Wash capped berries; drain.
Sprinkle with sugar and toss with sour cream, in desired amounts.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Butter casserole dish; layer deboned chicken in bottom of dish.
Combine broth, soups and Veg-All; pour over chicken. Combine Bisquick, milk and melted butter; pour over soups.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup in medium saucepan until a thread is spun.
The mixture falls off the spoon as a fine thread or hair-like (285° to 290° on candy thermometer).
Add peanuts and stir continuously until mixture turns a golden, slightly brown color.
Remove from heat and immediately add butter, salt and soda.
This will result in a foamy mixture.
Stir in quickly and spread on buttered cookie sheet or board.
Allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix carrots, onions and green pepper.
Pour dressing over carrots and let stand in covered bowl for 2 or 3 days.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak
peas overnight; drain.
Bring 1 quart of water to a boil and
add
peas,
ham,
onion and bay leaves.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add rice
and simmer until rice is tender, adding more water,	if necessary.	When
peas and rice are tender, remove bay leaves and adjust seasoning.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs. Add bananas, honey and milk.
Sift together baking powder, salt and flour.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Put batter in greased muffin tins or cupcake pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: zucchini sausage pie
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water and drain.
Saute sausage and drain.
Combine zucchini and sausage with remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons cheese.
Pour into greased pan and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and walnuts into a large bowl. Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake for 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Place on wire rack until cool.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, soups, sour cream, corn and salt. Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine macaroni and beef mixture.

title: grandma's old timey tea cakes
directions: *Is 3 to 4 cups of flour (measure 1 cup at a time).

title: chuck o dillie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a mixer.
Then add egg yolk and vanilla until smooth, but not to be over mixed.
Ice while warm with fondant icing with chunky peanut butter added. Cut like brownies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar and oil.
Fold in egg white.
Add flour and beat.
Cover with dish towel and let rise until double.
Turn out on floured surface and knead thoroughly. Make into rolls and let rise until double (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 375° to 400° until brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix together.
Bake or cook together on stove.

title: baked chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat until smooth the remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: In a blender put eggs, onion and sherry (optional).
Run blender on liquify for about 5 seconds.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add venison hamburger, sausage meat, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Then place in buttered loaf pan which has been lined with strips of bacon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Degrease pan drippings, strain, pour over loaf and serve.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients for sauce.
Slash fat edge off ham at 2-inch intervals.
Brush meat liberally with sauce and let stand 1 hour.
Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes per side, turning once and brushing with sauce.
Serves 8.

title: apple loaf
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs well, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in tightly covered baking dish.
Combine 3/4 cream, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and seasoned salt; mix well. Pour over chicken and cover.
Marinate 3 hours or overnight.
Put flour in plastic bag.
Put chicken in and coat well.
In bowl, beat 2 large eggs with 1/2 cup cream.
In another bowl put corn flake crumbs with garlic and basil.
Melt butter in large casserole dish. Take chicken from flour; coat well in eggs and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place chicken in casserole dish; cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove; cover chicken with onion and bell pepper. Add 1 cup water and cover; cook 20 minutes more.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix and bake in Bundt pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with onions and mayonnaise.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese, then top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted oleo over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan (large).
Cook to 130° on candy thermometer.
Add raw peanuts and cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Add soda and salt.
Beat a few minutes and pour in buttered pie pans (about 6 pans.)

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Middle will appear rather soft.
Cut after cool.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix
vinegar,
sugar,
peanut
butter and eggs and cook until thick
and cool.
Add milk and pour over sliced bananas; add ground peanuts.

title: batter for fish fry(no fat - baked)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable spray.
In a shallow dish, stir mayonnaise, mustard and 2 tablespoons water until blended and smooth.
In a second shallow dish, combine cornflake crumbs, bread crumbs, wheat germ, salt, pepper, thyme and oregano.
Dip each fish fillet first into mayonnaise mixture and then into crumb mixture to coat thoroughly. Shake gently to remove excess crumbs.
Arrange fillets on a cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until golden brown.

title: leek soup
directions: Saute leeks in butter.
Peel and cut potato into tiny pieces. Boil in water.
Add leeks and seasonings.
Simmer about 10 minutes until veggies are soft.

title: skillet tamale pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and cook over medium heat separating with a fork in small pieces until it loses its red color.
Add onions, corn and tomatoes (undrained).
Slowly stir in corn meal, salt, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir over low heat for 10 minutes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and hot and well browned; about 45 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo(low-fat)
directions: Place flour in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, or until dark brown, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove skillet from oven; set aside.
Combine chicken and water in a large Dutch oven; cook for 20 minutes, or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and broth from Dutch oven; set aside.
Combine onion, green pepper, celery, garlic and 1/3 cup chicken broth in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add browned flour and 1 cup chicken broth; stir until blended.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cut up oranges and use juice and oranges to mix cake mixture. Add oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Cook at 350°.
Bake in 3 greased pans for about 30 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add pumpkin, evaporated milk and slightly beaten egg and stir until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pastry crust.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted 2 inches from the edge comes out clean.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and margarine thoroughly.
Beat egg, lemon rind and extract into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Remove to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and marshmallows.
Let stand overnight. Mix together rest of ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
(Beautiful red color; great at Thanksgiving!)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled pretzel mix. Mix the jello and boiling water.
Add the frozen strawberries. When partially set, spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix Sour Cream & Chives Instant Potatoes according to package directions. Add additional 1 cup sour cream to potato mixture. Lightly grease casserole dish. Layer 1/2 of the potato mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle 1 can of onion rings and 1 cup cheddar cheese on potatoes. Cover with remaining potato mixture. Bake for 1/2 hour in a 350 degree oven. Sprinkle remaining cup of cheddar cheese mixture on this baked mixture and then sprinkle remaining can of onion rings on top. Place back in oven until onion rings are nice and brown.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press in 8-inch pie pan.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together until smooth.
Mix Dream Whip by directions on box.
Mix Dream Whip with cream cheese mixture.
Pour in pie crust.
Spread pie filling over cheese mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place heavy duty foil in pan; sprinkle dry onion soup in bottom.
Set meat on top of soup and pour mushroom soup over roast.
Fold foil tightly around roast.
Cook at 300° for 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Frost cake.
Refrigerate 24 hours before cutting.

title: strata squares
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan and spray with Pam.
Spread hash browns on bottom and layer other ingredients.
Pour egg mixture over all. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes, at 350°, then uncover and bake 25 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Mix brown sugar, vinegar and water.
Cut pork into small pieces.
Pour mixture over pork and cook well.
When done, shred meat and add 1 small bottle ketchup and mustard.
Cook.

title: healthy heroes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; let stand 30 minutes.
Slice buns in half horizontally.
Pull out soft inside of both top and bottom halves, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells (reserve crumbs for other uses).
Line each bottom half with a lettuce leaf.
Spoon mushroom mixture evenly onto lettuce, using a slotted spoon.
Cover with remaining lettuce.
Arrange ham, turkey, tomato slices and cheese on lettuce.
Place top halves on sandwiches; wrap in plastic wrap. Chill up to 2 hours.
Cut in half to serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add all ingredients except pintos.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir in pintos.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Cook onion in oleo in pan until starting to brown; add beef and stir until it loses its red color.
Add rice; stir well.
Add celery soup, water and soy sauce.
Stir well.
Put in long casserole dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 of onion rings, onions and soup.
Stir in green beans.
Place other 1/2 onion rings on top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken & dumplings(heritage recipe)
directions: Stir 1 c. broth in flour, salt, and baking powder and add egg.
Stir until thick enough to roll out.
Roll on floured surface.
Cut in 2 inch squares and drop in boiling broth and cook 10 - 15 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until stiff dough forms.
Beat real good for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425° or until golden brown. Melt margarine and brush over biscuits before removing from pan. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Serve warm.

title: butter mochi
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients in another bowl and then combine together.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop all vegetables well.
Mix ingredients together.
Store in quart jars in refrigerator.
Garlic salt may be used.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Layer the cake, strawberries and bananas. Combine the jello and hot water.
Add the lemon juice.
Let cool until lukewarm and pour over the cake mixture.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Mix the pudding according to directions.
Pour over other ingredients and cover with the Cool Whip.
Serves 40.

title: low-cal chop suey
directions: Brown hamburg in large pan, add chopped onions and chopped celery.
Add beef broth when needed a little at a time, add bean sprouts and mix well, 1 minute.
Serve with brown or white rice.

title: rock road brownie
directions: Mix together and frost.

title: skeen's beans
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet and drain. Saute onion and bell pepper in skillet. Add ground chuck, pork and beans, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Cook on low for 15 minutes. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well; place in 8 inch iron skillet.
Bake at 375 degrees for one hour.

title: calico cauliflower salad
directions: Combine vegetables in bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly with vegetables.
Chill 2 hours, mixing gently several times.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In pan, melt butter, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil; mix in bowl sugar and flour.
Pour cocoa mixture over sugar and flour.
Mix well, then add 1/2 cup buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, eggs, cinnamon and soda.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix mashed bananas with beaten egg, oil, honey, vanilla and water.
In another bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in center and pour in wet mixture all at once.
