Stir just until moistened; batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased or non-stick tins 2/3 full.
Regular muffins bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Mini-muffins bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar kisses
directions: Slice sugar cookie dough according to directions.
Remove wrapping from kisses and place one in the middle of each cookie. Push lightly into dough.
Bake according to cookie directions. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: beer-batter mushrooms
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Let sit 1/2 hour, then stir again.
Allow to rest.
Dip mushrooms in batter. Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Use as a side dish or an appetizer.

title: applesauce quesadillas
directions: Place 2 tortillas on ungreased baking sheet.
Spread each with applesauce, sprinkle with cheese and cinnamon.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Brush with butter, sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 400° for 7-8 minutes.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Cut up potatoes, onions and cabbage according to people served.
Cook in large cooker until potatoes are done.
Add gravy mix and cut up corned beef.
Serve with cornbread.

title: oatmeal pie #2
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Toss chicken with salsa.
Spread tostada shells with cream cheese.
Top with chicken mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Serve with additional salsa, if desired.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake
mix,
margarine, egg and nuts, press into 9 x 13-inch pan
and top with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: piccalilli
directions: Mix chopped vegetables with salt in a non-reactive bowl.
Let stand, covered, overnight.
Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: chocolate-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: greek vegetable salad
directions: Have all the vegetables cooked and seasoned.
Cut into small pieces (diced).
Save the 1 egg for garnish.
Also dice the shrimp or the cold cuts.
Mix all with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Put in a serving dish.
Cover with additional mayonnaise, forming a round or oblong shape.
Decorate and garnish with sliced eggs, capers, olives, beet slices, etc.
Let your imagination be your guide.
I like to use homemade mayonnaise for this salad.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and pepper together.
Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Dip slices in beaten egg, then in cornmeal mixture.
Fry in hot oil until nicely browned.

title: chocolate chip bites
directions: Blend shortening, sugars, flour, baking powder, salt, soda, egg yolks and vanilla.
Spread dough on 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add 1 cup brown sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread on batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: norma's hot fudge sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot water, combine cocoa, sugar, salt, cornstarch, corn syrup, cream and milk.
Stir constantly while cooking over medium heat.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool before placing in airtight container for storage in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream the butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Add oatmeal to creamed mixture, alternating with flour, soda and salt.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread topping on while hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and spread on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Spread over rice.
Add water chestnuts and chicken.
Combine milk, cream of chicken and cream of onion soup. Pour over entire mixture.
Spread Cheez whiz over all and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all the ingredients with the drained noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a large baking dish.

title: earl's popcorn balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; cook to hard ball stage. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine.
Pour slowly over popcorn. Mix thoroughly to coat popped corn.
With hands well coated in margarine, form balls quickly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to slow boil.
Simmer 1 hour. Makes 1 quart.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk and pudding in bowl.
Beat until well blended; let set 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and candy.
Spoon into crust and freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Keep remaining pie in freezer.

title: major's french blueberry pie
directions: To stiffly beaten egg whites, add next six ingredients. Shape into a crust in a buttered pyrex pie dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool thoroughly.
Break up cream cheese and add powdered sugar, vanilla and Dream Whip.
Whip until stiff.
Put in crust and top with 1 can blueberry pie filling.
Chill 5 hours or overnight.

title: neapolitan dessert
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cool, add second layer.

title: gran's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together baking powder, salt and flour; set aside.
Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Turn dough out onto a "heavy floured" surface and knead 4 or 5 times, adding flour as needed.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
For all over golden crusts, allow space around each biscuit.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon frosted pecan cookies
directions: Stir 1 cup butter to soften; add 3/4 cup powdered sugar, milk, flour and cornstarch.
Cream until well blended; chill.
Place small spoonfuls of chopped pecans 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Shape dough into small balls and flatten each over a pile of pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in water, oats, coconut and candy. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
16 dozen.

title: lo-cal broccoli and cheese stuffed potato
directions: Top baked potato with steamed broccoli, sour cream and hard cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in medium baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar. Stir in flavoring and oil; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold in yolk mixture into whites.
Fold dry ingredients into egg mixture.

title: a luscious punch
directions: Make quart and freeze.
When ready to serve, add 3 bottles ginger ale to each quart.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Chop peppers and onions, including greens on onions.
Press garlic and Tasso.
Slice sausage into 1/2-inch slices.
Boil pepper, onions, garlic, sausage and Tasso in large pot with 2 1/2-quarts water.
The longer the better.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with a lattice top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes until nicely browned.
Serve slightly warm.

title: banana apricot nut bread
directions: In bowl mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar, apricots and nuts.
Combine banana, milk, egg and butter.
Stir into dry ingredients and blend.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Melt over boiling water.
Combine sugar, syrup, eggs and vanilla. Blend sugar mixture into butter mixture and turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: "pimento cheese dessert"
directions: Drain pineapple and dissolve jello in boiling juice from pineapple.
Refrigerate until mixture just begins to jell.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad oil; mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into 1/2 inch hot oil in a large skillet. Flatten patties to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cook to a golden brown, turn over and brown other side.

title: a-z bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add to the sugar mixture whatever you are using as your A-Z
and the vanilla.
Mix well.
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Pour in batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, garlic and beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables. Heat oil in frying pan and add steak and brown.
Simmer about 30 minutes until tender.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Cook vegetables until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water and add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: dog-gone good cookies for rover
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let cool before giving to your dog.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until beef is browned.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except green beans.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add green beans, continue simmering 10 minutes more.

title: low-fat oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 slices.
Brush cut surface lightly with melted margarine.
In a plastic bag, combine Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, paprika and onion powder.
Add 8 potato slices at a time to bag. Shake to coat.
Spray an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating.
Arrange potatoes in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: oliver family brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in reserved liquids with meat; bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 or 3 hours.
Yields about 6 to 7 quarts.
This recipe freezes well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mash bananas.
Add vanilla.
Combine ingredients. Pour into 3 small loaf pans, 4 x 7-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: clusky
directions: Brown chopped meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and cheese.
Boil noodles and add to other ingredients.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: anything bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add anything moist and mix.
Add the flour with the soda, salt, powder and spices.
Mix. Add flour to make consistency a bit thicker than a cake mix.
Bake at 350°.

title: firecracker salsa(for goodness taste)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate, covered, 2 to 3 hours to blend flavors.
Adjust ingredients and seasonings to taste.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Fold sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt into whipped cream; add remaining ingredients except salad dressing.
Spoon into paper muffin cups; freeze until solid.
Unmold on lettuce; top with salad dressing.
Yield:
18 small servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger and fry.
Put hamburger and onions in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients, except for toasted bread. Mix together.
Tear toast into pieces and put on top of casserole.
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender, drain, then mash. Add all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker meal or bread crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done; remove peeling and mash well.
Mix with powdered sugar and peanut butter until thick enough to roll in balls.
Form balls; place on waxed paper and refrigerate until serving.

title: calico slaw
directions: Combine chilled vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
In separate chilled bowl, whip cream until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pie filling and chill for several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: black olive spread
directions: Soften the cream cheese and add mayonnaise, garlic powder and nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring all ingredients to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour mixture over popcorn, mixing well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pecan pies or tarts
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter. Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 pies or 16 tarts.

title: creole chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil until brown.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, heat butter.
Saute onion until tender.
Add garlic powder, seasoned salt and seasoned pepper. Return chicken pieces to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until chicken is cooked.
Serve over hot white rice.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 8-inch deep greased pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Toothpick should come out clean.
Enjoy.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Heat together brown sugar and butter until sugar dissolves. Add cooked carrots; cook over medium heat, turning carrots until well glazed, about 12 minutes.

title: frankfurter bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles, drain and return to kettle.
Stir in cheese, milk, oleo, flour and salt.
Pour into greased 12x8 inch dish.
Combine franks and remaining ingredients and spoon over noodles.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: chicken in sour cream(or kura pieczona w. kwasnej smietanie)
directions: Beat egg and cold water.
Cut chicken in pieces.
Dip in flour, in egg and water and then in bread crumbs.
Brown in butter.
Put in baking pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in oven and bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Heat the sour cream to liquify.
After chicken has baked 1/2 hour, pour a little hot sour cream over each piece.
The cream will be absorbed by the chicken. In 15 minutes, add more sour cream.
Repeat this method until all sour cream is used up.
Bake chicken for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach rice balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
On greased baking sheet, arrange balls and bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: jeff's fish fry
directions: Get your corn oil as hot as you can!!
A Fry Daddy is very handy.
This is the key:
hot oil!!
Roll your fillets in this seasoning mix.
It is great seasoning.
Drop your fillets in the hot oil.
Watch carefully.
When brown, remove out of oil and drain excess oil off on a paper towel.

title: green tomato slices
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt, pepper and sugar.
Dip very green firm tomato slices into mixture to coat both sides; fry in hot butter or oil a few at a time until golden brown.
Add more butter or oil as needed.
Serves 4.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Add onion, mushrooms, or fresh to taste.
Saute garlic.
Add soup (don't add water), paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all together.
Add noodles and 2-3 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook until noodles are done.
Add 1 cup sour cream before serving.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in order.
Combine rest for filling. Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 filling; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple-nut toss salad
directions: In a bowl, combine oil, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Add apple and onion; toss to coat. Add lettuce, walnuts and Blue cheese; toss gently. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat.
Toss three cups pre-flavored bread stuffing with 1/2 cup melted butter and spoon over top of carrots.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken simple
directions: Make sure chicken breasts are clean.
In microwave-safe casserole dish, add 2 cups rice; cover with water (approximately 2 cups).
Place chicken over rice.
Spread tomato soup over chicken. Season to taste.
Cover and microwave on High for approximately 25 minutes.
Serves 4.
Simple but good.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Blend.
Boil these ingredients and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Beat eggs; add dry ingredients, then vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter, then add mayonnaise to taste.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes small.
Cook in enough water to cover potatoes. When tender, add margarine, salt, pepper, chicken soup and water. Bring to a boil.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Grease 2 (1 lb. size) coffee cans.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake and cool completely.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Refrigerate.
Place one cake layer in 6-quart punch bowl.
Add, in layers, one-half of ingredients in following order: pudding, pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple and nuts.
Add other cake layer and rest of ingredients.
Add whipped topping at the end of each layer.
Garnish with nuts, cherries or coconut.

title: salted pecans
directions: Coat iron skillet with Wesson oil.
Preheat oven to 300°. Remove skillet.
Add pecans.
Stir.
Reduce temperature to 200° to 250°.
Add margarine; stir often.
Spread nuts on brown paper. Sprinkle with salt.
Keep in tight sealed tin or glass jar sealed with foil.
Can store in refrigerator.

title: ron's chicken ritz
directions: Place chicken in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream on top.
Place asparagus on top of sour cream.
Add mushrooms and then spread mushroom soup on top.
Combine butter and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole and top with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (saving a little of the Mozzarella to sprinkle on top).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie or can make up to 32 ounces of macaroni by multiplying by 4.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly brown on top at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Frozen shrimp may be used.
Drain and dry thoroughly.

title: stuffed mushroom caps(serves 8)
directions: Wash mushrooms, breaking stems out of caps.
Place caps on sided cookie sheet; discard stems.
Brown sausage and onions in frypan on medium heat.
Drain excess fat.
Add cream cheese and blend with onions and sausage.
Turn burner off and cool for 5 minutes.
Scoop into mushroom caps.
Heat oven to a broil.
Place cookie sheet on next to top rack.
They are cooked when rim of mushroom caps are browned, usually 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot. Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Only the stuffing can be frozen! Men can't resist these!

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat and add beaten egg; mix well.
Cool.
Combine marshmallows and nuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over them and mix well.
Shape into two rolls and coat with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: date cupcakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let cool.
Add eggs and beat, then add sugar, flour and salt.
Last, add nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Drop ingredients into bowl.
Mix.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Meanwhile, prepare sauce.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Do not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and bread crumbs.
Heat through.
In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine sauce and macaroni. Toss to coat evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kim's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with fresh cilantro.
Garnish with pimiento and dry dill.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill (3 hours).

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add condensed milk and butter.
Mix well.
Add pecans and marshmallows to chocolate mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch waxed paper-lined pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: orange tapioca pudding
directions: Take pudding mixes and jello, mix together, add 3 cups water. Boil 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Cool.
Fold in the mandarin oranges and add Cool Whip.

title: japanese fruitcake 2
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, using methods and cooking times given in Japanese Fruitcake 1. Put 1/3 of the batter in pan.
Add to remaining 2/3 of batter raisins, dates, citron, orange peel, lemon peel, figs and nuts.
Divide this batter between two pans. Bake.

title: white beans and smoked gar
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Discard water; add fresh water to beans and boil.
Add salt meat (which has been preboiled about half an hour), tasso, vegetables and seasoning.
Boil for about 2 hours until smooth gravy has formed.
For a thicker gravy, smash some of the beans.

title: pineapple and cheese dish
directions: Mix cornstarch, juice from pineapple and enough water to equal 1 cup, sugar and egg.
Bring to a boil.
Add pineapple chunks and cheddar cheese.
Some of the cheese will melt.
Arrange in baking dish and cover with marshmallows.
Bake at 350 for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: waverly caramels
directions: Place Waverly crackers tightly together on a large cookie sheet (13 x 15-inch).
Put 2 sticks of butter (must be butter) in a saucepan with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Cool slightly.
Do not stir.
Pour over crackers.
Cover with 1 cup pecans or walnuts.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat undiluted soup until warm (do not boil).
Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water.
Add to soup.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Stir in celery, onions, green peppers and crab meat.
Pour into a greased 1-quart mold.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: savory economy pot roast
directions: Place roast on heavy aluminum foil.
Combine soup and soup mix, pour over roast.
Wrap foil over roast.
Bake in roasting pan 4 hours at 325°.

title: dump cake
directions: Just dump 2 fruits (pineapple and apple) into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Place pats of butter or margarine over the whole mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
It will brown and bake.
Ooh...its good!

title: stir-fried chicken with mushrooms(moo goo gai pan)
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
Keep warm. Cut breasts in 1/4-inch strips on diagonal with knife almost parallel to cutting board.
In medium bowl, mix chicken, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, ginger root, sugar and garlic powder.
Set aside. Thinly slice mushrooms. Cut scallions into 3-inch pieces.
In a large skillet or wok over medium heat in 4 tablespoons oil, cook mushrooms and scallions until tender, 2 minutes.

Remove to bowl. Add 2 tablespoons oil to wok and over high heat, add chicken mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Return mushroom mixture to wok. Add peas and heat through. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange sliced bananas on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over bananas.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Makes 15 servings.

title: quick cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour batter into pan.
Drain cherries, reserving liquid.
Place cherries on top of batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: honey mustard
directions: Mix and serve with ham or turkey.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs; add to melted margarine.
Add sugar and flour mix.
Add milk and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until brown and set.

title: beverly knigh potatoes
directions: Put shredded potatoes in a baking dish.
Top with onion and butter.
Spread soup and sour cream over potatoes and butter.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400°, covered, 20 to 30 minutes and uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot or cold layered potato salad
directions: Reserve a few center egg slices for garnish.
In 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish evenly layer 1/3 of the potatoes, carrots, another 1/3 of the potatoes, the zucchini, the remaining 1/3 of the potatoes, the unreserved egg slices and the tomatoes.
Evenly drizzle with dressing.
To serve cold, cover and chill to blend flavors, several hours or overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: *For lemon cake, use lemon flavoring, for walnut use walnut flavoring, for plain use vanilla flavoring, for orange, use orange flavoring and for chocolate, use vanilla flavoring and cocoa.

title: pennsylvania dutch cabbage and meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper; mix well. Shape into medium-size meatballs. In large pot, place cabbage, water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer. Drop in meatballs; cover and simmer till cabbage is tender and meat is done. Recipe can be doubled or tripled.

title: touchdown punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon slices in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Pour into mugs. Garnish with lemon slices.
Hot punch may be poured into thermos jug and taken to the football game.
Yields 12 servings.

title: olive dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and dates in large pot and bring to boil. Add vanilla flavoring to this mixture.
Mix Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour the sugar mixture into the dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and coat with 4x sugar.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Beat egg yolks; add to mixing bowl, along with milk and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice in another bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
While beating, fold into batter.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place in a shallow pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve warm or chilled with powdered sugar dusting on top.

title: chicken lagasne
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix together Alfredo sauce, milk and oregano.
Mix together chopped chicken, artichoke hearts, bell pepper, onion, garlic and mozzarella cheese.
Spread thin layer of Alfredo sauce on bottom of 9x13 pan.
Spread one layer of lasagna noodles over this.
Top with half of chicken mixture.
Repeat layers, starting with half of remaining sauce.
After layering, pour remaining sauce over top of lasagna.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking an additional 15 minutes or until bubbly on top.
Allow to sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: franks and corn bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients, mix well. Transfer to a greased 9 inch square dish. Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions, stir in cheese. Drop by spoonfuls onto bean mixture. Bake uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: divinity
directions: Cook
the
sugar, corn syrup and water without stirring until mixture
forms a hard ball (spins a fine thread).
Pour slowly into
the 2 egg whites which have been stiffly beaten. Beat
until mixture loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts. (Maraschino cherries may be added, if desired.) Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper, lifting and twirling to form peak on each mound.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Cut stalks off mushrooms.
Clean out caps.
Set caps aside. Wash thoroughly and finely dice remaining mushroom pieces.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add garlic and diced mushroom pieces.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and cheese.
Heat until thick.
Cool, then stuff caps.
Bake in covered dish at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon;
remove
skin

and bones, then flake with fork. In	small bowl, mix cream cheese; blend in lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and liquid smoke (this is important).	Check seasonings; might need more salt.
Combine
pecans
and
parsley
and spread on sheet of waxed
paper.
Turn salmon out onto this mixture and turn this way and
that	until all sides are coated.
Wrap in waxed paper
and chill
thoroughly
before using.
The spread will spread nicely when chilled.
Makes 20 servings.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 5 metal loaf pan.
In medium bowl, with fork, mix buttermilk, melted butter and eggs until blended.
In large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With fork, stir buttermilk mixture and corn into corn meal mixture, just until blended.

title: dean's favorite cheese and ham ball
directions: On a cutting board, separate ham, slice by slice; lay back on top of each other, making one pile.
Take a sharp knife; cut pile into 12 to 16 pieces.
Turn board; cut pile again into 12 to 16 pieces, cutting ham into little square pieces.
Put in medium bowl; stir to separate ham.
Add cream cheese; stir together with ham pieces.
Mix in onion powder and seasoned salt.
Scrape from board onto a plate or serving platter; shape into a ball. Sprinkle paprika over ball, if desired.
Place crackers on plate around cheese ball.
Spread cheese and ham on crackers with knife. Enjoy!! This works great as an appetizer!

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except nuts.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Pie will puff and then fall slightly.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a 10-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry pepper, onion and garlic until tender-crisp.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of beef until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining beef.
In same skillet, combine soup, soy sauce and ginger.
Return reserved vegetables and beef to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
To serve, arrange rice on platter.
Spoon mixture over rice.
Makes about 5 cups or 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine all ingredients at low speed, blending thoroughly.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8-inch square baking pan and bake at 375° until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Rinse in cold water.
Let stand 3 tablespoons vinegar while preparing other ingredients.

title: sue's easy fruit pie
directions: Spoon pie filling in each tortilla; roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Combine sugar, water and oleo.
Microwave this mixture until dissolved thoroughly.
Pour this over filled tortillas. Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Put row on Twinkies in the pan.
Put whipped cream over the Twinkies, then add the pineapple over the whipped cream.
Put bananas over the pineapple, then put the rest of the Twinkies over bananas.
Add more whipped cream.
Put it in the refrigerator until it is cold, then it's ready to eat.

title: mexican cowboy stew
directions: Pour bacon grease into large skillet; add onion, meat and brown.
Add other ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 hours over low heat.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as you add them.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until done.
The batter is very stiff.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken until done.
Arrange pieces in 9 x 13-inch greased pan (you may choose to debone chicken first).
Sprinkle on onions, spices and Velveeta cheese.
Sprinkle on 1/2 package Doritos (crushed).
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups in blender. Pour over chicken mixture.
Place remaining Doritos on top (either whole or crushed).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in beaten egg and next four ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vichysoisse
directions: Put all except chives in blender until smooth. Refrigerate until very cold. Chill serving dishes, then sprinkle mixture with chopped chives.

title: red's barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain good.
Crumble corned beef into mixture.
Add catsup, chili powder, brown sugar and water. Stir well.
Add flour to thicken.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all in a medium saucepan over very low heat, stirring frequently until mixture forms a ball.
(Mixture will thicken slowly at first.)
Remove from pan and knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and margarine in frying pan.
Do not add water.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.
Mix soup, rice, cheese and salt with other ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered saltine cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Set aside.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip. Add to butter mix (use a large bowl).
Layer in large bowl or flowerpot with crushed Oreos on top. Add gummy worms.

title: crabmeat and cream cheese ball
directions: Mix in bowl and form into a ball.
Refrigerate.
Cover with seafood cocktail sauce and serve with Waverly Wafers.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and salt; cook to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Butter a large baking pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: hershey's chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: chunky potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins in boiling water until tender, about 35 minutes.
Peel and slice while hot.
Meanwhile, cook bacon in a skillet until crisp; remove, crumble and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion, celery and pickle and saute until tender.
Blend in vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and sugar. Gently stir in beans and bacon; heat through.
Turn beans into serving bowl; add hot, sliced potatoes.
Toss and serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Let ingredients soak for 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, or until brown, at 350°.

title: ricotta pineapple muffins
directions: In a measuring cup, place the egg and add enough oil to make 1/2 cup.
Add the egg and oil mixture to the Ricotta cheese and mix until smooth.
Add the crushed pineapple.
In a separate bowl, combine the dry ingredients and blend gently.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: crab mold
directions: Put water into a kettle and sprinkle gelatin over cold water. Dissolve over low heat.
Combine cream cheese, soup and onions. Cook over low heat until smooth.
Add gelatin and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased 4 cup mold.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate cake to the max
directions: Allow butter and eggs to stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, lightly grease bottoms of three 8-inch by 1 1/2-inch round cake pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper.
Grease and lightly flour bottoms and sides of pans.
(Or grease and flour one 13-inch by 9-inch by 2-inch baking pan.)
Set pans aside.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Heat water, onion, salt and Tabasco to boiling.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in black-eyed peas and bacon.
Heat to serving temperature and eat immediately.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Combine marshmallows, walnuts and graham crackers in a large mixing bowl.
Place butter, sugar, salt, vanilla, egg and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Pour over marshmallow mixture; mix thoroughly.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Cool.

title: pork and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight,
then
cook
until
soft.
Drain. Mix rest of ingredients
together and cook a few minutes, then add to beans and mix well.
Put
in
jars
and
process
1 1/2 hours in pressure cooker at 10 pound pressure.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tsp. and bake at 375°F for 10 minutes.

title: popcorn crisp
directions: Butter long baking dish.
Crumble coconut macaroon cookies. Layer fruit on crumbs:
pineapple tidbits, pears, peaches, black sweet cherries (half) and bananas.
Drain fruit.

title: fish with rice - sayyadieh
directions: Clean fish and cut into large chunks.
Fry the fish in olive oil until browned.
Remove fish to platter and fry onions in the same oil.
When onions are golden, remove from oil.
Wash and drain rice.
Place 1/3 of the fish and all the onions, raisins and seasoning in cooking pot and add 3 cups of water.
When water begins to boil, add the rice and cover.
Cook over a medium-low flame until rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed (about 30 minutes).
Turn the fish and rice upside down on a large platter. Melt butter and pour over rice.
Garnish with pine nuts.
Serve with parsley tahina salad (Bakdounsieh).

title: white sugar taffy
directions: Boil until brittle stage when dropped in cold water. Put on buttered platter. When cool enough to handle, pull as long as possible. The more you pull it, the less sticky it will be. Be sure to butter your hands before you pull the candy. It is more fun to have someone pull the taffy with you and you can each take an end of the rope of taffy.

title: sweet and sour sauce for egg rolls
directions: Mix cornstarch and water in medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients to saucepan and stir to mix.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: beaver cleaver's venison stew
directions: Brown meat (with oil) in big pot and remove meat, leaving oil. Add onions, celery and garlic to pot and cook until tender, stirring continuously.
Put flour in and stir well.
Add boiling water with beef bouillon and stir.
Always stirring, good for bow arm muscles.
Add tomatoes, beer, spices and browned meat and stir until well mixed.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 1/4 hours, stirring between beers.
Add carrots and spuds and cook 30 minutes, covered.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir zucchini, mushrooms and onions in butter over medium heat until tender.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut wedges; serve warm.
Serves 6. No crust needed.

title: peanut butter buckeyes
directions: Mix well together the first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of large marbles.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put into freezer a half hour before dipping.
Melt the chocolate with the paraffin in pan (double boiler).
Spear each ball with toothpick. Dip into melted chocolate.
(Only dip far enough to leave a little circle of the peanut butter showing, so they will look like buckeyes.)
Place on wax paper; cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and cover with stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add sugar, oil, and applesauce. Stir well until combined.
Stir in raisins and pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: I boil potatoes with jackets on.
Pare and boil potatoes until done, but firm.
Cool.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and fat from pan.
Place 1/4 cup bacon fat in the pan.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until thick, about 5 minutes.
Slice cool potatoes and combine with bacon, celery, onion, green pepper, eggs and pimentos.
Pour dressing over potato mixture and mix lightly. Place in casserole.
Serve warm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: persian clusters
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add salt and sugar.
Beat until shiny.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon or tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Stir together next 5 ingredients. Put in casserole and bake 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with wooden spoon until well blended.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans or an angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake test comes out clean using toothpick.
Cool on rack for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese chili sauce
directions: Stir cream cheese and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Add chilies, lemon juice and garlic salt.
Mix well. Serve over hot baked potatoes or vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all beans except pork and beans.
Brown bacon, hamburger and onions.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pocket sandwiches
directions: Add all ingredients except for cheese.
Split pita bread, put mixture inside, sprinkle cheese on top.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook rice while making jambalaya or use leftover rice.
Melt margarine in heavy 3-quart pot.
Saute onion, celery, pepper and garlic until onion is wilted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, stirring constantly, 3 minutes over low heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and sugar.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne. Cook uncovered over medium-low heat 20 minutes; stir occasionally. Add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink and cooked, 3 to 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water and add.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Mix with cooked rice.
Add green onion and parsley.
Mix again.

title: "mom's out of town" casserole
directions: Boil noodles; drain and rinse.
Cook spinach and drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato paste, Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt and oregano to meat.
Mix well.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Grease two 2-quart casseroles.
Layer ingredients in this order: noodles, butter, cheese mixture, spinach, noodles, butter and meat layer on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on each casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: princess pineapple bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple and orange rind. Pour batter into 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan lined with baker's parchment brown paper and well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost, while hot, with Nutty Cream Cheese Frosting. Yields 48 (2-inch) squares.

title: barbara's neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cream sugar, cream cheese, margarine and 2 eggs. Blend in vanilla flavoring and coconut.
Pour over first mixture. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: surprise in the mail spinach lasagna
directions: Mix the last 6 ingredients. Grease a lasagna pan. Layer noodles in pan followed by layers of the cottage cheese mixture, Monterey Jack, spinach and Parmesan. Bake, uncovered, in a 340° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: old fashioned chicken 'n noodles(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in 3-quart glass casserole.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over.
Microwave on simmer for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Remove chicken from broth; stir in noodles.
Re-cover and continue cooking on defrost for 12 to 14 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Remove chicken from bones.
Return chicken meat to broth. Re-cover and cook on simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in a large bowl the shortening, butter, peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Sift in a separate bowl the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix flour mixture in with the butter mixture. Form dough into balls.
Press into crisscross shape with a fork. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine other ingredients, except cracker crumbs, to make sauce.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except
eggs
in
saucepan. Simmer over
low
heat
for 10 minutes.
Arrange eggs in two 1 quart jars.
Pour 1 cup vinegar mixture over eggs in each jar. Cover tightly
and refrigerate overnight.
Eggs may be stored up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook mushrooms	and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender; remove from butter.
Add remaining butter.	Mix flour, salt and
pepper;
dredge meat in this mixture.
Brown quickly in butter.
Sprinkle
remaining flour over meat.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire
sauce;
heat through.
Stir 2 tablespoons flour into
sour cream; stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion;
cook
over	low
heat until thickened.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add baking powder, salt, soda, vanilla and flour.
Last, add dry ingredients, cooked raisins, oatmeal and cereal.
Roll in balls, place on cookie sheet and press slightly.

title: braised turkey legs
directions: In large skillet, bring all ingredients to boil.
Cover and simmer 1
to
hours or until legs are tender, turning legs
occasionally.
Cool.	Remove meat from bones and cut	 in pieces.
Strain
broth.
Delicious	for
sandwiches, salads, hash, creamed turkey or used in chowder.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange 6 slices of bread in it.
Cover with cheese slices.
You can add anything else you want to, such as crumbled bacon, pimento, spinach, diced cooked vegetables, tuna, meat, shrimp, diced ham, etc. (leftovers work great!).
Cover with remaining 6 slices of bread. Beat the eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, can be overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 minutes until puffed and browned.
Let sit for about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in covered casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes longer with dish uncovered.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend marshmallow cream and Philadelphia cream cheese.
Serve with fresh slices of apples, bananas, oranges or pineapple chunks.

title: lemon cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Blend together and mix 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased and floured pan 9 x 15 inches.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together and pour over Rice Chex. Stir to coat well.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in paper bag.
Add Rice Chex to bag and then the rest of the sugar.
Close bag and shake until well coated.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a baking dish.
In a bowl, mix together the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter, then spoon fruit into middle of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: eight-layer jello
directions: Total 8 boxes of Jell-O.
Layers will be in order of flavors given.

title: bible cake
directions: Note: Leaven in the Bible means yeast or baking powder.

title: chilled asparagus salad(our family's favorite salad!)
directions: On individual salad plates, arrange lettuce.
Add a thin slice of large purple onion (or chop it).
Add one or two slices of cold tomato.
Add strips of the chilled asparagus strips on top of the tomato slices.
Drizzle the Ranch dressing on top or your favorite dressing.

title: cranberry congealed salad(this is a nice holiday salad!)
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and pineapple together.
Mix.
Add water to jello and let cool,
When cooled, mix with cranberry mixture, gelatin and Coke.
Add nuts.
Pour into lightly greased mold and chill until set.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar, peanut butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and peanuts.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm. Cool in pan.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in a deep dish and smooth evenly on bottom.
Do the same with pineapple over top of cherries.
Then pour cake mix on top of pineapple.
Place little squares of butter on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over butter squares, then bake for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup. Boil 15 seconds. Fold in order: peanut butter, vanilla Special K. Mix and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper until cold. Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Cut up small onion.
Mix squash, onion, cream cheese, butter and mushroom soup together.
Put bread stuffing on top.
Cook 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool and eat.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container and use as needed.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix jello.
When it starts to thicken, mix in other ingredients.
Whip, then let set.

title: oatmeal muffins(mother's circle cookbook, 1920)
directions: Soak oatmeal in the sour milk overnight.
In the morning, add rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.
Cookies can be frosted.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: In a bowl, mix and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bonnie butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a baking pan(s), one 13 x 9 x 2-inch or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.

In a large mixer bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Beat 5 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally. On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake oblong 45 to 50 minutes, layers, 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Frost with your favorite frosting.
Enjoy.

title: chicken saltimboca
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 pieces of waxed paper until about 1/4-inch thick.
On boned side of each breast, place 1 slice Mozzarella cheese and a dash of Italian herb seasoning.
Roll up. Dip each piece in melted margarine.
Then roll in mixture of bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Stir with spoon until well blended.
Add egg, milk, extract and flour.
Continue to stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar. Bake for 10 minutes.
Once out of the oven, press Hershey's Kiss into center.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: miniature fruit cakes
directions: Dredge fruit and nuts with half the flour.
Cream sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine remaining flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in miniature muffin pans or in miniature paper baking cups at 275° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: "eagle brand" milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix until well blended. Cool at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.
(Makes the same as one regular Eagle Brand milk.)

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix in order as given.
Makes a delicious fruit dip for all fresh fruits.

title: stewed okra
directions: Wash and chop okra.
Dice onions.
Heat bacon drippings on medium to high heat, add chopped okra.
Stir until okra stops stringing.
Add onion, sugar and half of tomatoes, cut up.
Place other half tomatoes and juice from tomatoes in food processor until liquid.
Pour in with other ingredients.
Stir.
Cook until okra is tender.
Serve over white rice.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and Karo syrup in large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Cook mixture until it spins a thread a foot long.
Beat egg whites until stiff, pour cooked mixture slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla, beat until mixture loses its gloss. Drop onto waxed paper by teaspoons.
You may add nuts.
Also use this recipe for icing.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix only.
Pour 1/2 into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Bake about 15 minutes until top begins to bake.
Melt margarine, caramels and Eagle Brand together.
Blend well.
Pour caramel mixture over hot cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Pour rest of cake batter on top.
(Nuts if desired.)
Finish baking as directed on cake mix.
Refrigerate.

title: easy pudding milkshake
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add pudding mix and ice cream. Cover.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately.
Mixture thickens as it stands. Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage and boil until tender.
Brown hamburger, sausage, onions, garlic and pepper.
Drain cabbage; add meat and tomatoes. Cook.
Served best with Mexican cornbread.

title: lady olivia's royal nut torte
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until stiff; beat in sugar and vanilla.
In a smaller bowl, chop nuts; crush crackers and add baking powder. Stir well.
Fold nut mixture into egg white mixture.
Bake at 350°
in a greased pie pan for about 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant 5 to 10 minutes or until tender, drain off water.
Mix all ingredients together with eggplant.
Pour into greased one-quart casserole dish or baking pan.
Bake at 425° approximately 30 minutes.
Cut cheese while eggplant is cooking and put a little grease on top of casserole before baking.
If larger portion is desired, double recipe.

title: blueberry bran breakfast muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine bran cereal and milk. Let stand about 5 minutes or until cereal softens. Add egg and oil. Beat well. Add flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened and combined. Gently fold blueberries into mixture, taking care not to crush berries. Pour into muffin tins lined with muffin papers. Bake in 400° oven 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm with butter and honey.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Add chopped cabbage and onion. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Simmer until cabbage and onion are done.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in fat.
Sprinkle with salt.
Peel potatoes and halve.
Rub with lemon juice and place on pork chops.
Press 1 clove into each prune.
Arrange prunes and pineapple on potatoes. Add pineapple juice; cover and cook on high until steaming.
Turn to low for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese, lemon juice, pimento and mushroom soup.
Pour over broccoli.
Roll crackers into melted butter.
Cook casserole in a 350° oven until bubbly. Cover with buttered crumbs and cook about 10 minutes.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add salt, beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onions.
Cook on stove until bubbly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with biscuits that were cut in half lengthwise.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage roll
directions: Fry sausage out of casing.
Cool sausage in strainer.
Whip egg and mix with sausage and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll dough out, wide as a piece of tinfoil, long as a cutting board.
Put sausage and cheese mixture on dough.
Sprinkle onion salt, garlic salt and lots of Parmesan cheese.
Roll up and seal sides.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at a time, until brown (at least 30 minutes).

title: no bake cookies
directions: Have ready in a bowl, peanut butter, cocoa, and oats and vanilla.
Bring to a boil sugar, butter, and milk.
Boil exactly one minute.
Mix dry ingredients.
Drop by spoon and let cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all up, except cheese. Pour half of mixture in pan. Lay cheese on top. Pour rest of the mixture on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Then combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder; spread thinly over cooled crust.
(Cut into squares.)

title: springtime soup
directions: Saute leeks and onion in butter; add water, potatoes, carrots and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rice and asparagus.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Add spinach and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in cream and bring almost to a boil.
Flavor improves if made ahead of time.
Heat to serve.
Do not boil.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot or casserole dish. Put in oven, heated at 350°, and bake for 1 hour.
Or, in crock-pot, cook on medium heat for 1 hour or until broccoli is tender.

title: banana nut icing
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread over cake.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook ground chuck.
Chop onion; place in bowl and microwave with margarine.
Butter casserole dish.
Place noodles, onion and ground chuck in dish.
Mix the 2 sauces together; pour half over beef.
Over the top, spread the cheeses (that have been mixed).
Place pepperoni on top.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Beat in eggs and add buttermilk, melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie shells. Place pies on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until set and golden brown.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients;
beat egg slightly.
Form in large ball. Let cool before
using.
This
may	be divided and part used later; it freezes
well.
Use
any kind of fruit.
I cook my fruit and add
a	little	cornstarch with sugar to thicken. Do not punch holes with fork.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Mix together broccoli, onions, soup, rice and cheese. Bake in greased casserole dish for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, flour, sugar and spice together.
Blend well. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Add dots of margarine and milk over top, then cover with top crust.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Mix soups, sour cream and tomatoes.
Set aside.
Crush Doritos and put in casserole dish. Add 1 layer of beef, 1 layer of cheese and 1 layer of soup. Repeat, ending with Doritos.
Heat at 350° until hot.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onions in shortening until meat is white and onions are done.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: black-eyed pea skillet dinner
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, garlic and green pepper over medium heat until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: pineapple ham glaze
directions: Combine and pour over ham.

title: aunt theresa's lake charles dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve with chips.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Blend cheese until smooth, and mix in horseradish and 2 salts. Add dried beef, shape into ball, wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
When firm, reshape and roll into parsley. Cover and refrigerate.

title: mehlbuttel
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar. Add salt and milk. Stir in sifted flour (all at once) and beat until smooth and free from lumps. Add melted butter and egg whites that stand in peaks.
Dip a tea towel in boiling water, then into cold water. Wring dry and place in a pan with edges of cloth hanging over the edge.
Pour the dough into cloth and tie 1 1/2-inches above dough to allow expansion, be sure to tie firmly.
Have a large kettle of rapidly boiling water ready.

Gradually ease mehlbuttel into kettle and keep boiling constantly for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from water at once. Cut string and ease nice plump mehlbuttel onto a platter. Cut with heated knife. Serve with cooked ham and prune or raisin sauce.
Flavor with a stick of cinnamon sugar
and lemon juice. If you wish, a bit of wine may be added.
Thicken the sauce with cornstarch.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in long pan. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix dry ingredients together. Make a well in dry ingredients and add wet ingredients, apples and pecans. Mix just until moistened. Place in greased muffin pans. Bake about 20 minutes. Makes 8 jumbo muffins.

title: polish sausage
directions: Brown
sausage, green pepper and onions.
Add tomatoes, sauce, garlic,
sugar,
salt and pepper.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Add oregano. Simmer another 1/2 hour. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Soak 8 cucumbers in 1 cup of pickling lime for 24 hours.
Rinse and drain until water is clear, about 3 times.
Into roasting pan, measure 9 cups vinegar and 9 cups sugar.
Let dissolve.
Add 2 tablespoons pickling spices in a cloth.
Tie and put in mixture. Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Cool until mixture boils for about 35 minutes.
Turn out fire and let stand 24 hours.
After the 24 hours, bring the mixture to boil.
Have jars boiled and ready. Place in jars and seal.
When cool, tighten lids.
Now you have pickles.
"Ummmm good."
Store in cool dark place.
I learned to make these pickles from Granny Hannah (Mrs.
Mary Hannah).

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 to 10-inch quiche or pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, chives and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese melts and mix is heated.
Serve with nachos, veggies, etc.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger; drain off fat and set aside. Cook bacon and crumble.
In same skillet, using a little of the bacon drippings, saute onion until tender.
In a crock-pot, mix all ingredients well.
Cover and set on high until mixture is hot, then set on low and cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: super breakfast or brunch dish
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Arrange in baking dish the eggs, cooked peas and water chestnuts.
Mix and beat gently the chicken soup, sour cream, milk, instant onion and sherry.
Add pimientos.
Season to taste and pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Can make day before and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french fried potato skins
directions: Using a vegetable peeler, cut long thin strips or spirals of potato skin.
Reserve potatoes for later use.
Place potato skins in a bowl of ice water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Using a deep fat fryer, electric frying pan, wok or heavy saucepan, pour oil to 3 inch depth.
At this temperature, a 1-inch cube of bread will turn golden brown in 20 seconds.
When oil is ready, drop in chilled potato skins, a few at a time.
Fry until skins are golden brown and crisp, about 1 minute.
Repeat with remaining potato skins.
Drain well on paper towel.
Sprinkle skins with salt or choice of seasoning.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 appetizer servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all the above ingredients.
Mix Well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve chilled.

title: tangy salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Thin to desired consistency with milk.
Makes two cups.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Drain peas and smash smooth.
Place in a 1-quart bowl or microwavable dish and add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir well and pour into a serving bowl.
Serve with corn chips or raw vegetables.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix all other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot all the way through.

title: seafood spread
directions: Saute celery, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add mayonnaise.
Pour lemon juice over shrimp and crabmeat.
Add to first mixture.
Put into greased casserole and top with crushed saltines and Parmesan cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Waverly crackers.
This recipe can be prepared ahead, frozen and baked prior to serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: On large cookie sheet, spread tortilla chips to cover.
Brown the ground meat and sprinkle over the chips.
Mix the soup and picante sauce and pour over the ground meat. Cut the onion and cheese (in chunks).
Sprinkle over the casserole.
Put in medium oven until cheese melts and onion is done.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop vegetables (coarse).
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand over night.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boil.
Simmer 3 minutes. Fill hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yield:
about 8 pints.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and raisins in bowl. Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar well and pour over the broccoli mixture.
Cover and marinate several hours or overnight.
Before serving, add the bacon.

title: chinese meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; simmer.
Mix remaining ingredients and add 1/2 of sauce mixture, mixing well.
Shape into loaf; pour remaining half of sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft oatmeal cookie
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix in soda, cream of tartar, flour and oatmeal.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Rinse.
Melt butter. Add oil, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Then turn and broil 5 to 10 minutes on the other side.

title: fettucini alfredo cream sauce
directions: Brown the garlic in the oleo or butter. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook about 20 minutes or until thick (like gravy). Stir some sauce through cooked fettucini (or linguine). Add remaining sauce and stir through noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potato rice soup
directions: Heat oil in pot.
Add garlic and cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix with hands in order given.
Roll into little fingers. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 275° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: On 100% power cook 5 to 7 minutes until crisp-tender the spinach, berries, turkey and asparagus (drain and cool).
Mix dressing, orange peel and orange juice and pour over greens.

title: apache pilot chili
directions: This is so quick and easy that even a "fighter pilot" can do it.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine dates, oleo and sugar.
Cook at medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture blends into a paste.
Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well.
Cool until you can handle.
Roll into small balls with fingers, pressing well.
Roll in powdered sugar and cool.

title: cabbage soup or "just good soup"
directions: Cook ground beef in 5-quart kettle until it loses pink color but not brown.
Drain off fat.
Add the cabbage and water, green pepper, bouillon cubes, cayenne pepper and kidney beans.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Then add tomato juice and cook 45 minutes.
Add water if too thick.

title: low-fat banana-date cake
directions: Mix nonfat milk and vinegar and let stand until thickened. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir to blend.
Lightly beat eggs and egg white.
Add to flour mixture with bananas, pureed dates, soured milk, vanilla and nuts.
Stir just until blended.
Pour into a 12-cup Bundt pan sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: bev's cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger; place in large pan hamburger, onion and celery.
Add cabbage and tomato sauce; cook 10 minutes.
Add rice, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Cook minutes.
Quick way to make cabbage rolls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugars, then eggs and vanilla.
Mix together baking soda and flour; mix all together.
Put on cookie sheet.
Press each one flat with back of a floured fork.
Bake about 8 minutes.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: *Cubed, cooked chicken can also be used.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a large buttered pan, add a layer of dried beef (may be freshened if you wish) and boneless chicken breasts.
Combine sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: swiss steak del rio
directions: Spread butter on 20-inch piece heavy-duty foil.
Cut Swiss steak into serving pieces.
Place on foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes, cayenne, salt and pepper.
Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over steak. Wrap foil over and double fold edges to seal.
Place on baking pan.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Roll back foil.
Let brown 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add salt, ginger, cinnamon and eggs. Stir in the potatoes and water.
Bake in oven at 325° in a buttered dish for 45 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well.
Divide into four parts.
Roll in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Slice and bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dressing, mustard, dill weed, onions and celery.
Add potatoes and toss lightly to mix.
Serve at once or chill.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat whipped topping, lemonade concentrate and condensed milk in a large bowl.
Pour into crust and chill one hour before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients except juice.
Add juice while whipping until mixture is smooth and creamy.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar and cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in chopped nuts.
In small bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in milk and vanilla and stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spoon batter evenly into greased and floured Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
(Cinnamon-sugar mixture may be sprinkled on top of mixture before baking.)

title: my favorite cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in sour cream.
Press graham cracker crust firmly to bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until firm.
Turn off oven and leave door ajar for 1 hour, leaving cake undisturbed until cool.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with your favorite toppings.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Chop green peppers and chili peppers in blender with a little of the vinegar.
Boil sugar and vinegar 15 minutes; add color and Certo.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Pack in small jars and seal. Serve on Ritz crackers, meat and etc.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk over low heat. Add marshmallows, stirring constantly. Cook until smooth. (Be careful not to burn.) Remove from heat. Put graham crackers into paper bag and crush with a rolling pin. Mix crumbs with fruit and nuts. Add marshmallow mixture; blend well. Line bowl with waxed paper. Pour cake mixture into bowl and press down firmly so that it takes the shape of the container. You may decorate with fruit and nuts on top if you like.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Mix together well the first 6 ingredients and add the remaining ingredients. Pour into a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Put pie filling and pineapple in baking pan.
Put dry cake mix over.
Pour butter over cake mix.
On top of this put pecans and coconut.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dutch kraut
directions: Wash kraut one can at a time.
Chop onion and add to kraut. Put in a heavy pot and cover.
Add water just to top off kraut and boil on medium heat for 4 to 5 hours.
You may have to add more water while cooking.
Cook down dry.
Grate potatoes.
When kraut is cooked dry, place potatoes on top of kraut.
Fry bacon.
Pour hot bacon grease over kraut and potatoes.
Crumble bacon on top of kraut and potatoes and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Delicious with dried beans and corn bread.

title: snow balls
directions: In a pan, stir chocolate and milk on low heat until chocolate melts. Remove the saucepan from heat.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Put the pan in refrigerator for 10 or 15 minutes.
Cool.
Roll into ball.
Roll in coconut.

title: ham and broccoli au gratin
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package except use 2-quart casserole and omit butter.
Stir in broccoli and ham and bake uncovered at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix the oleo and cream cheese. Add vanilla and almond flavorings.
Add salt and powdered sugar.
Mix.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and amount of water directed on package and let cool.
Prepare lettuce for salad.
Add taco mixture, olives, cheese and Doritos.
Mix well and add salad dressing.

title: gazpacho verde
directions: Combine soup, milk, vegetables and olives in blender.
Blend for 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice and sour cream.
Blend until smooth.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Yield:
8 to 12 servings.

title: dinah's cheesecake
directions: Reserve 5 tablespoons crumbs for the top.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Add drained oranges, pineapple and 2 heaping tablespoons of Cool Whip.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: crunchy two-style chicken
directions: Put cornflakes in plastic bag and crush them with the rolling pin.
Then dump them into a pie pan.
Melt butter.
Roll each piece of chicken into the butter.
Then coat the piece in the cornflake crumbs.
Place in a big enough pan (they shouldn't be touching each other), then sprinkle paprika and seasoned salt over.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: tabooly salad
directions: Wash vegetables and chop fine. Wash and soak wheat 10 to 12 minutes. Squeeze water from wheat and add to vegetables. Add olive oil, salt, pepper, lemon juice and tomatoes. Mix well.

title: arizona beans
directions: Brown green onions and peppers in bacon grease.
Drain juice from beans, except pork and beans.
Mix all beans, onion, pepper, bacon, brown sugar and chili sauce.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour or longer, if desired.
Can be cooked in crock-pot as well.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: Pour soup into 2 individual casserole dishes. Divide water into both. Float on each 1/2 English muffin (toasted). Top with 1 slice Mozzarella cheese on each. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes. Lavishly sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, melt oleo.
Add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Add hash browns; mix gently but well. Place in large casserole.

title: pear salad
directions: Place pear halves in a single layer on a platter of your favorite greens (lettuce, baby spinach, etc.). Put a dollop of Miracle Whip in the center of each pear half. Sprinkle generously with the two cheeses.
