Top with cherries, if desired.

title: oven-blackened salmon
directions: Line broiler pan with foil and spray with butter spray. Squeeze the juice of 1/2 lemon over fillets.
Sprinkle top of each fillet generously with Old Bay seasoning and spray lightly with Pam.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 7 minutes.
Turn over and repeat on other side.

title: party chicken(serves 8)
directions: Pound chicken breasts and place one slice of cheese on top. Fold the chicken breast pieces and wrap with bacon.
Secure with toothpicks.
Put shredded beef in bottom of shallow dish. Place breasts on top. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over all. Place in refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
(Men may eat two!)

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Pour on crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine pecans, sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: meat loaf(serving size:  8.  preparation time:  2:00)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Brown cracker crumbs in butter; set aside.
Drain oysters, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Place 1/2 of crumbs in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add oysters, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Combine half and half and reserved oyster liquid; pour over cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: honey butter
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Stir in honey and peels.
Serve with bread or biscuits.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Serve with a variety of fresh fruits.

title: dig deep salad
directions: In a large, deep bowl, layer lettuce, onions, pepper, celery, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Layer crackers in a clear glass bowl. Mix pudding with 3 cups milk. Layer pineapple, bananas and strawberries over crackers. Pour pudding mix over fruit. Cover with Cool Whip. Make ahead to serve later. Serves 8.

title: cole slaw
directions: Prepare dressing in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Pour hot liquid over cabbage mixture.
Cool.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Cut green pepper in cabbage.
Cool and serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Form into balls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mama's strawberry preserves
directions: Pour boiling water over strawberries; let stand for 2 minutes. Drain.
Combine berries with 4 cups of sugar; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add 2 cups of sugar and stir well.
Return to heat and boil 5 minutes.
Pour in shallow pans and let stand overnight (shake occasionally).
Ladle into sterilized jars and seal.

title: ground beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef in oil; drain.
Stir in parsley, carrots, celery, soup mix, salt and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are almost tender.
Add noodles; cover and cook until noodles are tender (about 10 minutes).
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Cover meat with water.
Add salt.
Cook slowly until meat is tender. Then shred.
Cook onions and celery in butter until golden brown.
Add rest of ingredients, meat last.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours. Stir frequently.
If sauce gets too thick, add meat broth.
Make day before serving, as sauce flavors meat.
Use kaiser rolls, hamburger or snowflake rolls.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over low heat.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Stir often; cook until onion is yellowed. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste, a pinch of sugar and basil.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally and partly breaking up tomatoes.
Slice each shrimp in half, lengthwise, and add.
Reheat.
Serve over hot rice.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easter bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted Crisco and yeast.
Add flour, a little at a time, until dough doesn't stick to hands.
Put in large greased bowl. Cover with several dish towels and let rise. Shape into loaves and let rise again.
Place loaves on greased cookie sheets and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients after mixed.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place about 6 cookies to each cookie sheet.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Crumble 1/3 cake in bottom of punch bowl. Cover with layer of pudding, layer of pineapple and bananas.
Place ring of cherry pie filling 1 inch from outside edge.
Will look like a donut.
Fill inner and outer edges with Cool Whip.
Repeat twice.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on bottom of pan, overlap and press to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and buttermilk mix.
Add dash of lemon juice; spread on cooled crust.
Add vegetables, chopped, such as broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, tomatoes, green pepper and fresh mushrooms.
Press lightly with cheese mixture (shredded Colby cheese).

title: sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover with water.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Cook over low heat for 4 to 5 hours, adding water as needed.

title: simple beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat; add enchilada mix according to package directions.
In small amount of oil, quickly fry tortillas, just enough to soften.
Place on paper towel to drain.
Shred cheese.
In 9 x 13 baking dish, place 1/3 of chili in pan bottom.
In center of tortilla, place small amount of beef mixture and cheese.
Roll up and put in baking dish.
When dish is full, pour remainder of chili over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream, oil and instant pudding together with beater.
Batter will be very thick.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top of cake.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Section wings at joints, discarding wing tips.
Combine flour, salt, sugar, cornstarch, rice flour and ajinomoto.
Beat eggs until well-blended.
Add with onions and soy sauce to dry mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: crunchy pie(this pie freezes well.)
directions: Beat egg whites stiff. Continue beating.
Add baking powder and sugar slowly. Fold graham crackers and nuts into mixture. Pour into a 9-inch greased glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool pie. Cover with half the whipping cream, whipped and sweetened.
Place in refrigerator overnight or for at least 4 hours.
Add the other half of the whipped cream to top when you serve.

title: chicken pot pie 1
directions: Boil chicken in 2 cups of water until done; debone chicken and mix with broth, cream of chicken soup and Veg-All.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add potatoes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift the dry ingredients and blend the entire mixture.
Spread thin in a greased paper lined pan.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced apple cider(mulled)
directions: Put cider into saucepan.
Add the spices, salt and sugar; cover and heat very slowly to the boiling point.
Heat should be so low that it takes the cider about half an hour to come to a boil. Remove from heat, strain and serve steaming hot.
Serves 5.

title: ratatouille(good hot or cold)
directions: Use any amount vegetables desired.
Saute red and green sweet peppers for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add thick slices of sweet onions and thin slices celery.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Add chicken broth (fat removed); simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Add yellow and green squash; simmer 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, peas, margarine, garlic, hot pepper, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender, al dente, or to your taste.

title: vermont fruit salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in large serving bowl.
Pour sauce on top of fruit and toss lightly.
Cover and chill 4 hours.

title: sour cream mold
directions: Mix together.
Put in mold or pie dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add frozen strawberries or raspberries before serving.

title: cowboy rolls
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Overlap biscuits in round cake pan.
After coating all over with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle leftover cinnamon and sugar atop biscuits.
Melt margarine.
Pour over top of biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Soaked raisins may also be used.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon and add onions, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add beans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, then add Jell-O and boiling water.
Mix until melted.
Put in the marshmallow cream.
Mix in the pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Can use any kind of Jell-O.

title: squash pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with the dough. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl and beat until smooth and well mixed.
Pour into the lined pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat to 300° and bake for 60 minutes more.

title: chocolate mint ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill the rest of the way with milk.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: baked broccoli in rice
directions: Cook rice.
While rice is cooking, saute oleo and onion together.
Drain rice.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir in onion mix and broccoli and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes covered and the rest of the time uncovered.
Sprinkle with crumbs or potato chips.

title: easy honey mustard chicken
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package directions.
Pour 1 cup prepared dressing over chicken in large bowl.
Refrigerate 3 hours to marinate. Remove chicken from marinade.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: asian chicken and noodles
directions: Remove seasoning packet from noodles.
Bring 2 cups water to boil in large saucepan.
Add noodles and vegetables.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally; drain.
Meanwhile, heat oil in skillet over medium heat; add chicken.
Cook until done, about 8 minutes.
Stir in noodles, vegetables, stir-fry sauce and seasoning packet.
Can serve over chow mein noodles.

title: crawfish casserole(student favorite)
directions: Empty package of crawfish tails into bowl.
Do not rinse off fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add can of cream of mushroom soup and mix well.
Let stand while preparing additional ingredients. Prepare two cups of rice according to package directions.
Melt stick of margarine in 5-quart Dutch oven and saute onions and bell peppers about 5 minutes, until tender.
Add crawfish mixture.
Let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice (about 4 cups or to your liking.
Dish will be too dry if too much rice is added.) Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken in cheddar cheese soup
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Put 1/3 of mixture on bottom of baking dish.
Layer chicken breasts with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Peel potatoes and quarter.
Lay potatoes on top of chicken.
Cover chicken and potatoes with the remainder of soup mix.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2
hours, uncovered.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Arrange graham crackers on it. Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt oleo and add sugar; bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour glaze over graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Break apart before completely cool.

title: fruit salad and dressing
directions: Mix in a large bowl.

title: huevos rancheros(serving size:  4.  preparation time:  0:30)
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Cook onion, garlic and pepper until soft.
Beat eggs until light and pour into frying pan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly.
When eggs begin to harden, add picante sauce and salsa.
Continue to cook and stir until set.
Serve immediately.

title: seedy lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Beat together sugar, lemon peel and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 1 2/3 cups of the flour, the baking powder and salt; mix well.
Combine the remaining tablespoon flour and the sunflower kernels; toss lightly.
Stir into batter.
Pour evenly into prepared pans.
Bake 1 hour or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Let cool on wire racks 10 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Makes 10 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put all the vegetables in a small baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple and cottage cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool.
When cold blend in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish and refrigerate.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9-inch greased pie pan and chill for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Wash first three ingredients, cut up and place on top of each other in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Add frozen peas on top of lettuce.
Spread on mayonnaise, then sprinkle dressing mix on top of mayonnaise.
Add cheese and top with bacon bits.
Keep refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: buckhorn inn's broccoli salad
directions: In a 1-quart bowl, mix all ingredients until mixture is well blended.
Refrigerate.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put mashed potatoes in dish; top with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's best turkey dressing
directions: Heat turkey broth left in roaster after removing turkey.
This is the success of the dressing.
Add some broth from giblets, reserving some of this broth for your giblet gravy.
Add cornbread, crumbling fine.
Add stuffing mix.
Add salt, pepper, eggs, chopped onions, sage and well mashed liver.
About 30 minutes before dinner bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, on lower rack in oven.
Dressing is done when brown around edges.
Brown on top with broiler.

title: giblet gravy (optional)
directions: Heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over dressing.

title: mammy day's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes for each egg.
Add flavoring and flour slowly.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet hopping john
directions: Saute margarine, clove of chopped garlic and chopped onion. When cooked a little, add the chicken broth, the rice and black-eyed peas (drained and rinsed).
Can add crushed red pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
(I add 1 can chopped green chilies instead of red pepper and chopped ham.)
I had to add a little water.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie(power drink)
directions: Put bananas, strawberries and milk in blender.
Add ice-cream and ice.
Blend at medium speed for approx. 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve chilled.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix well; set aside for at least 2 hours.
Shape into balls with damp hands.
Dip into colored chocolate.
For Mounds bars, shape and dip into dark chocolate.
For Almond Joy, shape into balls.
Place an almond on top and dip into light chocolate.

title: grandma fahrenkrog's v-8 juice
directions: I can this mixture throughout the summer season when my tomatoes and peppers get ripe.
In large pans I fill with tomatoes, cut in half.

I then add to each pan 1 pepper (cleaned and cut in strips), 2 strips of celery, 1 carrot (cut up), 2 or 3 leaves of lettuce, 1/2 cup of beets (I use my canned beets), a good handful of watercress and a few twigs of fresh parsley or 1 teaspoon of dried parsley.
Cook this until heated, it doesn't have to be mushy.
Then take it while it's hot and put through a tomato press.
After running the vegetables through the press once, I then again take the skin and remains and run it through the press once more to get all the pulp out of it.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use well-greased 9-inch or 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top and salt.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Take foil off the last 30 minutes.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients until dough forms a ball. Shape dough by teaspoonfuls into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Dip glass into sugar and flatten balls. Bake about 8 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: jack daniel's rib glaze
directions: Mix well.
Makes enough for 2 racks of 7 to 10 ribs each.

title: manicotti or large seashells
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Remove from heat; drain off fat. Combine bread and milk and let stand 2 minutes.
Add bread and milk mixture to beef.
Stir in egg, Mozzarella cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; set aside.
Cook manicotti or shells according to package.
Spread 1 1/2 cups sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Fill manicotti/shells with beef mixture and place in single layer on sauce in prepared dish.
Cover with remaining sauce and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 manicotti or shells.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients, except oil and vinegar, in mixer and beat well.
Continue beating and begin adding oil slowly, not more than 1 teaspoon at a time, until mixture begins to thicken.
Then, add rest of oil, 1/4 cup at a time, alternately with the vinegar.
Add more seasoning if necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread after crust has been removed. Cut up into 2-inch pieces. Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Place bread in dish. Mix eggs and drained sausage together. Add milk and cheese. Pour over bread. Refrigerate overnight. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil. Remove foil and cook 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and put in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, pepper and parsley leaves.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: herb garlic bread
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the butter, thyme, rosemary, oregano and basil.
Heat over low heat until the butter is melted. Slice the bread and generously brush the butter mixture on each slice.
Sprinkle with minced garlic, Parmesan cheese and parsley. Bake in a 475° oven or under the broiler until lightly browned. Serves 6.

title: turkey cutlets with cranberry sauce
directions: Dip cutlets into flour to coat.
In nonstick 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat with olive oil, cook turkey cutlets, half at a time, until brown and have lost their pink color throughout. Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate and paraffin.
Roll into small balls.
Refrigerate a few hours.

title: texan quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Bake shell 5 minutes. Fill shell with quiche mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Place apples in 10-inch round cake pan.
Combine 1/2 cup granulated sugar and the cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.

title: easy applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans in a large mixing bowl. Beat on medium speed for approximately 10 minutes. Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 35 to 50 minutes depending on your oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir beans, soup mixture and almonds together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and onion rings on top. Bake until cheese bubbles, approximately 10 minutes.

title: chicken in cream sauce
directions: Layer casserole dish with dried beef.
Wrap 6 chicken breasts with bacon.
Mix 1 sour cream with can of mushroom soup, spread this mixture over wrapped chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chess square
directions: Mix butter, 1 egg and cake mix (will be crumbly).
Spread in bottom of 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs together with mixer.
Spread over top of cake mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together into mixing bowl.
Stir in egg, milk and bacon drippings, mixing well.
Fill 8 greased muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: raspberry bar
directions: Beat oleo with sugar until well blended.
Add combined flour and baking soda; mix well.
Blend in almond extract.
Stir in oats.
Spread mixture into bottom of greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch); spread with preserves to within 1/2 inch of outer edge of pan.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 22 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes about 20 bars.

title: helen's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 345°.
Cream margarine and cream cheese for 5 minutes.
Add all sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and 3 eggs, beat 1 minute.
Add remaining flour and eggs, beat 1 more minute.
Be sure batter is smooth.
Add the flavor and mix 2 minutes.
Pour into tube pan, greased and floured.
Cook in oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Melt stick of butter in 9 x 12-inch dish while mixing milk, flour and sugar. Pour into the melted butter.
Spoon the peaches on top of mixture. Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil until creamy.
Add soda, baking powder, salt, vanilla, zucchini, nuts and cinnamon.
Mix well. Add flour slowly until well blended.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until springs back.

title: jello coconut pudding cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, water and oil in large mixer bowl; blend.
Then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Set aside 1/4 cup coconut for garnish.
Stir remaining coconut into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and finish cooling on rack.
Brush top of cake with honey; sprinkle with reserved coconut.

title: chicken cups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased muffin tins or paper lined muffin tins.
Set in pan of water larger than muffin pan tray.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.
May be served on a bed of lettuce.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in refrigerator.

title: 90 minute yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Heat milk, water and oleo to 125°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1 cup flour; beat at high for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make dough soft.
Knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 parts.
Put into greased pan.
Put into cold oven with pan of hot water underneath.
Close oven, let rise for 30 minutes.
Remove water.
Cook 30 minutes at 375°.

title: colcannon(irish)
directions: Peel, boil and mash potatoes. Finely chop scallions; add to potatoes.
Pour on boiling milk and beat until fluffy.
Cook cabbage.
Chop finely and pour on melted butter.
Add to potatoes, chopped parsley, salt, pepper and cabbage and beat together well.

title: cheese logs
directions: Beat cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Trim crusts off bread.
Roll flat.
Roll each slice as thin as possible.
Spread on cheese.
Roll up into two logs.
Dip in melted margarine and roll into combined sugar and cinnamon.
Freeze.
Bake frozen in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rice consomme
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top layer is cheese and has browned.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Put pudding mix and sugar in top of a double boiler; stir in egg yolks. Put pan over simmering water and gradually stir in water. Cook slowly stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Add butter, and spoon mixture into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites, adding sugar gradually. Spread meringue completely covering pie to edge of pie shell.	Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese cake to die for
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar in a bowl thoroughly.
Add in cool whip.
Mix all together and spoon into crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before topping with your favorite topping.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add oil, vanilla and lemon peel.
Combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Wrap and chill dough for several hours.

title: cherry-lemon icebox tarts
directions: Let crusts sit at room temperature for 15 minutes before opening. Cut crusts into circles to fit mini-muffin pan (use cookie cutter, jar, etc.). Generously prick the bottom and sides of each crust with fork. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 425° or until just lightly brown. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk, oleo, sugar and salt in saucepan. Cook and stir until mixture comes to full boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate pieces, beating until melted.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cloud capped apricot salad
directions: Place gelatin in a large size mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
When mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites, fold in apricots and nuts.
Turn mixture into a lightly oiled 2-quart baking dish (12 x 1 3/4 x 1 3/4-inches).
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Cook rice; drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all together.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix with chopped vegetables.
Mix in seasoning and salad dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry okra in small amount of oil.
Add all onions, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cover with top and cook.
Cut sausage up into small pieces and cook in microwave oven long enough to rid it of most of the grease. Drain.
Add tomatoes and bay leaves.
Salt and pepper to taste to okra mixture.
Cover and cook.
Make roux in large pot.
Pour ingredients from skillet into roux.
Add water, shrimp, crabmeat, crawfish and sausage.
Bring to boil. Serve over rice.
An added treat is to add crawfish bisque heads. It cannot be beat.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg; mix well.
Chill. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 5.

title: delicious and easy red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour three 8-inch pans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs and cocoa into cake mix.
Add butter.
Stir in buttermilk until smooth.
Add food coloring.
Mix well until blended.
Divide batter among pans and bake until tops spring back when touched and cake shrinks from sides of pans.
Bakes in 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-knead herb bread
directions: In a large bowl combine whole wheat flour, sugar, seasonings and yeast.
Heat water, milk and oil to lukewarm (110° to 115°) in a saucepan or in the microwave.
Add to the flour mixture along with the egg.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Stir in the all-purpose flour by hand to form a stiff dough.
(Add a little more if it doesn't feel stiff enough.) Cover.
Let rise 45 to 60 minutes or until doubled in size.
Punch down dough (punch fist into middle) and place in a 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan that has been spryaed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherries on bottom of a greased long Pyrex dish. Sprinkle half of dry cake mix over cherries.
Mix the rest of dry cake mix with the nuts and sprinkle over.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti with bacon and peas
directions: Cook bacon and drain, reserving 1 Tbsp. grease.
Place bacon on paper towel to absorb grease.

Put reserved grease in skillet; add onion and cook until tender and golden, about 8 to 10 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions and, during last 2 minutes of cooking time, add frozen peas.
When pasta is cooked to desired doneness, drain, reserving 1 cup of the cooking water. Return pasta and peas to cooking pot and add Romano cheese, salt, pepper, bacon and onion.
Use some of the leftover cooking water to thin the Ricotta cheese and add to pasta.
The Ricotta cheese had to be thinned or it will not mix up well with the pasta.
Keep heat on low and heat thoroughly through.
Serve with a green salad and French bread.

title: uncle carl's salsa
directions: In large food processor, chop tomatoes, but not too much.
In small mini-chopper processor, chop onions and peppers until finely chopped.
Also chop garlic with peppers.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Peel, seed and cut up 6 to 6 1/2 pounds of pumpkin; cook with small amount of boiling, salted water until very tender.
Drain and mash.
Whip pulp with mixer until smooth.
In a large kettle, combine pumpkin, packed brown sugar, lemon peel and juice, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Cook and stir until mixture boils. Boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Ladle into hot, sterilized half-pint jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 8 pints.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix crushed cookies and 1 stick soft margarine; spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put in freezer to get hard.
Spread vanilla ice cream over cookies; put back in freezer.
Cook in saucepan, over medium heat, the Eagle Brand milk, 1 stick margarine and syrup until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool and spread over ice cream; put back in freezer.
Top with Cool Whip and freeze until hard.

title: cranberry strawberry jello
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together until done, about 30 minutes.
Make the strawberry jello, using 2 cups boiling water and 1 cup cold water.
Run cranberry mixture through food mill and add to jello.
Let chill until firm, preferably overnight.

title: sawdust dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry jello until jello is mixed up well.
Add cottage cheese.
Add drained crushed pineapple; mix.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour and serve.

title: mashed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with topping and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: alvina's coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° until middle of pie is firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Then mix in the chopped ham, shredded Cheddar cheese and a few parsley flakes until all mixed up.
Then cover and refrigerate overnight.
Then form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 1 hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours using a bundt pan.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom of pie shell. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings in a bowl; beat well.
Pour over bacon, cheese and onion.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 30 additional minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: indian bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and oil.
Mix well. Add enough water for stiff batter. Roll out on floured board. Cut with knife in squares. Deep fry in hot shortening.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar, or eat plain with honey.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough milk to make thick batter. Pour this into a very hot, oiled pan.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Mix all together and chill for one hour.
Roll into small balls.
Mold into berry shape with hands.
Roll in red sugar.
Dip cap end into green sugar.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Take out about 1 cup of mixture.
Spread remaining ingredients in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan to make a crumb crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and chili sauce.
Place with meatballs in crock-pot on low for 6 hours. Stir occasionally.
Great frozen and reheated!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Set aside.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Melt butter, syrup and brown sugar and let boil 1 minute. Remove from heat; add baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn placed in baking dish or pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir about every 15 minutes in that one hour of baking time.

title: peach cheese tart
directions: Arrange peaches in unbaked pie shell.
Beat cream cheese, milk, almond extract and eggs in blender.
Pour over peaches. Spoon over the melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden (about 1 hour).
Cool to slice.

title: spinach timbales
directions: Drain spinach; chop.
Add butter, salt, pepper, nutmeg and horseradish.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Combine with spinach mixture. Pack in greased timbale molds, custard cups or muffin tins. Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: boiled oxtails
directions: Clean oxtails and
place
in a boiling pot.
Cover with water and boil for 1 hour.
Add the other ingredients and boil for another 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Blend bananas, sugar and water in blender.
Add this to other ingredients (except 7-up or Club Soda).
Freeze.
If you use this as punch, take out of freezer about 1 hour before serving and add the 7-up or Club Soda.
Mix to make a slush.
You may also dip a scoop out and put in a glass; then pour 7-up over it. Approximately 50 servings.

title: low-calorie ambrosia
directions: Mix
coconut,
pineapple,
bananas and oranges with the yogurt.
Chill
for
several
hours or overnight.
The acid in the pineapple
will
keep bananas from turning brown.
Put in pretty bowl and garnish with the grapes and cherries.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add to the eggs, salt, pepper, cracker crumbs, pimento, cheese and milk.
Stir in the asparagus and pour into a greased 1-1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Pour butter over the top.
Set into a moderate oven 350° and bake, uncovered, until the custard has set, about 30 min.
You can assemble this dish ahead, pouring the melted butter over the top just before it at mealtime.
Or you can prepare and bake it ahead, and reheat it in a warm oven.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, bacon, onion and pepper in small bowl.
Separate crescent rolls into two rectangles.
Press seams together.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Roll, starting at longest side and seal.
Cut each roll into 16 slices.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix together well and fry in hot oil until brown.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 1 inch of lettuce.
Sprinkle peas over lettuce.
Mix salad dressing, onion and enough milk to make it spread easy.
Spread over lettuce. Sprinkle with bacon bits, then grated cheese.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: angel biscuit muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 500° until brown.

title: kahlua fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler on low heat until smooth. Hand beat eggs lightly.
Stir in brown sugar, salt, vanilla, syrup and
chocolate mix.
Mix 1/2 cup walnuts into batter.
Turn into pie shell.
Cover top of pie with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 350° in center of the oven until barely set in the center and pastry is light golden brown, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: "no fuss" black forest torte
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out and cool completely on wire rack. Slice cake to make 3 layers.
Place bottom layer on cake platter. Spread with about 1 cup whipped topping and add 1/3 of cherry pie filling.
Repeat with 2nd, then third layers.
Chill well before serving.

title: creamed scallops
directions: Wash and dry scallops.
Blend cornstarch with 4 tablespoons chicken broth.
Heat butter on medium/high heat and saute scallops for 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add onions and saute for 30 seconds.
Add sour cream and chicken broth, stirring occasionally. Add white pepper and m.s.g.
Simmer for 2 minutes, add scallops. Simmer for another 2 minutes to thicken broth.
Add cornstarch mixture little amount at a time, until desired thickness is achieved.

title: fruit cake
directions: Boil together about 4 minutes sugar, Crisco, water and raisins.
When almost cold, add cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, flour ,baking soda, eggs and wine.
Add fruit and dates.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the flour on fruit.
Grease long loaf pans (2).
Line with wax paper.
Grease again.
Add second layer of waxed paper.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 2 to 3 hours until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 long fruit cakes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix well Cool Whip, drained pineapple, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Freeze.

title: potato buns i
directions: Have all
ingredients
at
room
temperature.
Peel
and quarter potatoes, then cook
in salted water.
When potatoes are soft, sprinkle yeast into 1/4
cup
warm
water.
Drain
potatoes and reserve 1/4 cup potato water.
Mash
potatoes.
Add
lard
and sugar
to the potatoes, beating until lard is melted and the potato mixture is smooth.
Add the beaten eggs, potato water
and salt
and mix well.
Stir in the yeast, then half the flour. Knead
in
cups
flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let
rise
until
double.
Then turn dough and knead 2 minutes. Shape into
balls 2-inches in diameter and place in 3 greased 8-inch pans with
buns
barely
touching.
Cover
and
let
rise. Make crumbs with 1/4 cup
sugar, 1/4 cup flour and butter.
After cakes have risen 40 minutes, brush top with sweetened water (1 teaspoon sugar in 3 tablespoons water).
Top with crumbs.
In 350° oven, bake 20 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
In a large mixing bowl, blend oil, sugar, eggs, salt, baking soda and walnut flavoring.
In a separate bowl, sprinkle just enough flour over the apples, raisins and nuts to coat them.
Add remaining flour to oil mixture.
Fold in coated apples, raisins and nuts. Pour in prepared tube pan and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: lazy donuts
directions: Separate biscuits.
Use Coke lid to cut holes in biscuits. Drop biscuits in hot oil.
Brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Cover with powdered sugar.
You can cook holes also.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter on medium to high heat.
Dissolve sugar.
Add milk, bring to a steady boil.
Boil exactly 6 minutes.
Remove. Add vanilla and chips.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour mixture into ungreased pan.
Let cool until firm, then cut into squares.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, bay leaves, oregeno, salt and pepper to ground beef.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese to sauce and simmer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly and brown on top.
